    "Edited Writeup": "Jim lives in Chula Vista, California, in the same San Diego home for over 25 years. He has four children and two grandchildren. His oldest daughter, born in Heidelberg, is a former Army dentist now living in South Florida. His son, born in Germany, is a mechanical engineer living near Atlanta with his wife and one of his granddaughters. His third child lives in Northern California, and his youngest son, born at the Presidio, is a former Marine now working with him in San Diego and living with him along with his wife and his other granddaughter, whom he sees daily. He is an Air Force brat and Eagle Scout. His plebe company was G3, graduating from H4. A major highlight was his aviation service in Germany with the 207th Aviation Company, where he flew UH-1s and UH-60s and logged roughly 900 flight hours in three years supporting senior commanders and dignitaries across USAREUR. Additional highlights include command of an airfield at Fort Rucker, fixed-wing qualification, and serving in operational research and analysis roles. After leaving the Army in 1996 with over ten years of service, he joined Solar Turbines in San Diego following a JMO hiring conference. He began as a controls design engineer and spent nearly three decades with the company, progressing into systems development, project management, and long-term group management roles overseeing engineering teams responsible for gas-turbine control systems used in power generation and industrial applications. He majored in mechanical engineering with accreditation at West Point, soloed during cadet flight training, and graduated flight school as a distinguished graduate. He enjoys building scale aircraft models and advanced Lego kits, values family-centered activities, especially time with grandchildren, and maintains interest in aviation-related pursuits. He can be reached at jbbaumgardner61@gmail.com | 858-694-6514."
