    "Edited Writeup": "John Bencivenga resides in Tampa, Florida, where he works as General Counsel. Contact information includes 813-505-5398 and jbencivenga@verizon.net. He described his cadet experience candidly, noting that he disliked West Point and does not dwell on it, while recognizing the paradox that many of his closest and deepest friendships are with classmates, whom he considers reliable and worth supporting without hesitation. His cadet years are remembered less for specific highlights and more for the enduring bonds formed. His most significant Army experience consisted of a series of strong assignments, including service at Fort Ord and Fort Lewis, which he recalled as enjoyable and formative. After leaving the Army, he attended law school with a fellow G-1 classmate Rich Bradford, practiced law together for a period, then moved into an in-house legal role in 2003. He has served as General Counsel since 2007 and participated in the sale of a company to a UnitedHealth Group entity alongside a close H-1 classmate. His current interests include traveling, sports, and connecting with classmates who take their Catholic faith seriously, and he remains actively connected with members of G-1 through frequent communication. He and his wife Chrissy have four sons."
