    "Edited Writeup": "George Bond resides in Huntsville, Alabama, where he is retired and actively engaged in community and volunteer work. He described his cadet experience as a lot of work but with too many fond memories to count. As a member of the G1 “Activity Staff” he was known for organizing company parties and events, including a memorable one held aboard the Superintendent’s Yacht. His most significant Army assignment was commanding the Arctic Test Center in Alaska, a role he cited as one of the few in which he genuinely looked forward to going to work on Mondays. This was followed by service with the Missile Defense Agency in both Alaska and Germany, including technically demanding and diplomatically sensitive liaison work. After military service, he remained in Germany fielding missile defense systems in Poland and Romania. He retired completely at age 54 to prioritize time over income. His current interests include skiing, extensive travel, G1 get togethers, camping, fitness, and volunteer work. He is married to Lori Bond, a retired Army Nurse. Their two daughters currently live in Denver and their first grandchild is due in Feb 2026."
