    "Metro Area": "Tampa",
    "Edited Writeup": "Richard Bradford resides in Valrico, Florida, where he works in the legal field. Contact information includes 813-847-1793 and fsusma86@gmail.com. He described his cadet experience through specific moments rather than general characterization, recalling as a highlight the ceremony after completing hours as a firstie private when his TAC presented him his sabre at accountability formation, followed weeks later by travel to the Air Force Academy for the Army–Air Force game, where he declined a beer offered by an Air Force cadet in the dorms. His most significant Army assignment involved work connected to the School of the Americas while stationed at Fort Benning, where he participated in taking Salvadoran war veterans to Disney World and Epcot. After military service, he transitioned into the legal profession, including serving as second chair in a trial approximately one to two weeks after September 11. Rich left the Army in 1992 during the post–Cold War drawdown period. His current interests include golf, sports events, soccer, football, and travel, and his family includes a son serving as an Airman First Class at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base and a daughter expected to finish high school in 2026."
