    "Edited Writeup": "Mark Bradley resides in Shrewsbury, New Jersey, where he works in software, professional services, sales, and management while approaching retirement. Contact information includes 732-859-1184 and bradleymk5@verizon.net. He described his cadet experience with humor, noting that he spent his high school years trying to get into West Point and his cadet years trying to get out, remaining on academic probation for much of his time before graduating in the middle of the class and branching Aviation. His Army service included assignments with 4/7 Cavalry (later reflagged 5/17 Cavalry) in 2nd Infantry Division in Korea, followed by 3-101 Aviation in the 101st Airborne Division. After Desert Storm he served at Fort Rucker as an Instructor Pilot, primarily teaching helicopter gunnery, and later commanded an Air Traffic Control company before leaving the Army to start a family. After military service he worked for Booz Allen Hamilton supporting Army digitization initiatives in New Jersey, then transitioned to software firms in progressively broader roles. His current interests include golf, attending sports events, and travel. Mark and his wife Marianne have four children currently living across New Jersey, Mississippi, Delaware, and Mississippi."
