    "Edited Writeup": "Therese Brehm Therese Brehm lives in Carlisle, Pennsylvania with her husband Les. She has four children, stepdaughters 39 and 37, son 29, and daughter 27, and two grandchildren, ages 12 and 10. Her youngest daughter is currently a Captain and Apache pilot stationed at Fort Drum, surprising Therese and Les by following in their footsteps. Her first assignment after flight school was with 3rd MI Battalion at Camp Humphreys, South Korea, where she was schooled by crusty old Vietnam-era aviation warrant officers who presented her with an honorary warrant officer card when her tour ended. She stayed in the Army six years, leaving when she and Les started a family. After taking five years off, she worked as a manufacturing engineer before moving to IT Program Management for a government contractor during overseas assignments in Germany, Korea, and Kenya. When Les retired and they moved to Pennsylvania, she transitioned to IT Program Management as a civil servant, ending her career with DLA. She moved 14 times across four continents raising her children. She remembers fondly providing advice from a woman's perspective to her G3 gopher friends during evening counseling sessions, and they still maintain a big group text. She enjoys cooking, skiing, golf and travel as well as attending sporting and social events. She can be reached at tbrehm86@gmail.com | 703-795-5100."
