    "Edited Writeup": "Jack Callahan Jack lives in Minoa, New York, with five children, four currently serving in the military. His eldest daughter is USMA '20, a cyber officer with a master's in data analytics. His second is USNA '22, now at the Naval Postgraduate School studying computer science. His third is a firstie at West Point branching infantry, and his fourth is a youngster at the Naval Academy preparing for nuclear surface warfare. His youngest daughter Kate is in high school. No grandchildren yet. He served in Germany with the 74th Detachment in the Pershing 1A community under a German air base, handling theater nuclear responsibilities and translating German medical documentation for personnel reliability program reviews. He left the Army during the drawdown and completed medical school with help from West Point connections. After training in internal medicine and working in Watertown, he settled in Syracuse. He now works as an internal-medicine physician for the VA, running home-based primary care for elderly and critically ill veterans, including hospice patients. He grew up in Syracuse as one of seven children; his mother was a German national who survived wartime hardships. During his cadet years, he nearly failed out due to rock math after staying up all night folding socks, completed a Bolivia exchange trip, and was later flagged by two departments as a potential future faculty member. He remains active and engaged with Army-Navy games, Academy visits, and West Point family traditions. He can be reached at tracyjohnb6@yahoo.com."
