    "Metro Area": "Dallas",
    "Edited Writeup": "John Cannon John lives in Lucas, Texas. He and his wife have two adult daughters. One is a Texas A&M petroleum engineer working in oil and gas, and the younger is a University of Arkansas graduate working as a nurse at Baylor Hospital. He has four grandchildren: three little boys and a girl. All live in the Dallas area and he sees them most weekends. His plebe company was G4, graduating from H3. His earliest and strongest memory is upperclassmen demanding he \"just talk\" so they could laugh at his Alabama accent. Another foundational memory is learning that effort no longer mattered—only results. He recalls G-4 plebe year, meeting future lifelong friends, and realizing that people from all backgrounds are worth knowing. He remembers rugby injuries, 150-pound football, and the camaraderie of H-3. He never visited West Point before reporting. His Army highlights were flying brand-new Black Hawks from the Sikorsky factory to El Paso, then deploying them immediately for Desert Shield/Storm, supporting 3rd ACR with logistics flights, moving fuel and engines forward, and occasionally backhauling grateful Iraqi POWs. Later he commanded the only Black Hawk company in Hawaii, learning to fly night-goggles over water and running demanding inter-island missions. He left during the post-Desert Storm drawdown. Using a JMO hiring firm, he entered semiconductor sales in Dallas, rising quickly to general manager. He transitioned to healthcare IT, spending thirteen years in rehabilitation-software sales and becoming a subject-matter expert. He is semi-retired from a role in hospital communications technology. He sees himself as introverted and still surprised to have built a successful sales career. His approach is consultative: listen, answer honestly, follow through. Core Army lessons—do what you say you will do, and never expect others to do what you won't—remain the backbone of his professional style. He remains active and enjoys sports, particularly football and rugby from his younger days. His present life is oriented around family, work, and dogs. He can be reached at jlcannon4@verizon.net."
