    "State": "CO",
    "Metro Area": "Colorado Springs",
    "Edited Writeup": "Mike Chopp Mike lives in Colorado Springs, Colorado. He has two children: a daughter born in 1994 at Fort Bliss while he was deployed to Saudi Arabia on a PATRIOT ADA rotation, who works as an aircraft mechanic for a regional delivery company in Montana; and a son born in 1996, who works as a cybersecurity contractor for the government in Colorado Springs after serving in the Army in Germany as a Signal officer. His son is married but no kids yet. The kids' locations prompted Mike and his wife's move from Tennessee to Colorado. Mike was a plebe in A2 and graduated from I3. One of his best memories was when a yearling asked if he wanted to \"hang out\" and listen to the Asia album—he and another plebe had to get up on wardrobe doors between their arms and hang out while the music played. The other plebe asked to leave after the first song, but Mike stayed for several until the yearlings lost interest. He was enlisted Infantry for about three years before West Point and served as a PATRIOT Air Defense Officer after graduation. He joined a newly formed battalion at Fort Bliss that trained there for certification and deployment to Ansbach, Germany, volunteering for Advance Party to help prepare the battalion and B Battery for a smooth transition. He met his wife in Germany and they married in Denmark in 1990. He had two commands: rear detachment commander and later A Battery. His daughter's birth halfway through his six-month deployment to Saudi Arabia prompted his resignation, which surprised his wife, he loved serving but decided being a present father meant more to him. In 1995 he resigned his commission and hired on with a Swedish telecom company as a site manager. Within 10 months he was offered a regional operations manager position and was asked to do both operations and project management. He spent 28 years in the telecom industry as Project Manager and later Program Director for introducing new products into customer labs and live networks, with his last two years as a Proposal Manager. He retired at the end of 2022. He can be reached at m.chopp@yahoo.com | 629-252-4126."
