    "Edited Writeup": "Cary Clayborn Cary lives in Frisco, Texas. He has one child, his 19-year-old daughter Carly, currently attending Honors College of Charleston studying pre-law. His plebe company was I2, graduating from E4. His closest cadet friends were Chuck Luigs, Tom O'Brien, Dennis Kibby, Chris Cole, and Roger Knowles, and during firstie year he dated Kathy O'Brien. Firstie year he slammed into the ground during a stupid maneuver in a skydiving competition in Connecticut, but still jumped twice, producing air bubbles under his skin throughout his neck, chest, and stomach. He stayed in the ICU on oxygen for a week. Dennis Kibby told him just a few years ago that Keller didn't know if he would live and the red blotches all over his face were crazy. He's disappointed he doesn't have video of the accident or pictures of his face as both would be great social media material today. He also cherishes friendships with Tom McCann and Matt Pawlikowski (plebe roommates), Marc Harris and Rock Marcone (plebe/Beast roommates), Dan Schafer (initial medical sales days close friend), current DFW classmates Joe DePinto, Jesus Delgado-Jenkins, and Larry Hughes (also E4 brother), and dozens of other classmates he admires immensely. He served all five years in Mainz, Germany with 1/59th ADA supporting 8th Infantry Division, initially defending The Fulda Gap with an air defense umbrella, then became General's aide-de-camp to Tim Grogan (Class of '63) and John Landry (Class of '62). He had an amazing time in Europe before and after The Wall came down, but decided not to stay in and got his MSM from Troy University. He was pre-med at USMA and his MSM in business led to 30 years of medical sales overlapping with 20 years of financial industry interests (advisory, investments, analytics). His favorite job of all time was training minimally invasive heart surgery for five years with Heartport, putting the heart and lungs on bypass and conducting full heart surgeries without cracking the chest. Today he's involved in six different businesses, his current favorite two being Profit Inc (supporting the SMB community with advanced analytics) and Warrior Centric Health (teaching the commercial sector that they are taking care of veterans). He started playing golf at age 30 and has since played 774 different courses worldwide in 45 states and 17 countries. He's a member of Big Creek CC in Mountain Home, Arkansas which allowed him to join EPIC Golf Club and have access to almost every single private course in the top 250 including Augusta. He's traveled to 55 countries, though only once below the equator to South Africa, and is looking to travel to South America, Australia/New Zealand, and continue adding to the total to get to 100. He enjoys resort recreational diving, combining scuba with travel to unvisited Caribbean islands and the Asian Pacific. His right knee was replaced 18 years ago and left knee replaced in 2024, so he can ski again with no issue and is interested in occasional ski trips to offset golf and scuba. He can be reached at cary.clayborn.abt@gmail.com | 214-202-8939."
