    "Edited Writeup": "Ted Cummings Ted lives in Fairfax, Virginia. He and his wife Sonia have three adult children. Their eldest, Teddy, is a captain in the Army Reserve and works in finance for a Navy-related program at the Washington Navy Yard. Their daughter Shannon is a marketing manager at Carahsoft. Their youngest son Daniel recently graduated from Virginia Tech and works in sports performance analytics for U.S. Soccer, with periodic assignments in Atlanta.His aviation career was central: flying Cobras and later Kiowa Warriors, commanding a headquarters troop, and serving as a systems automation officer at the Hohenfels Combat Training Center. He deployed to Iraq, where he ran information-operations assessments and produced the metrics used in senior-level briefings during the surge. He retired as a colonel after 30 total years of combined active and reserve service. He transitioned into technology early, working for Fujitsu for more than a decade, then Dell, Unisys, and Salesforce/MuleSoft. He recently accepted a position as the Army account executive for Armis, a cybersecurity company. He met his wife in church in Fulda. He grew up as an Army brat with formative years in Panama. He enjoys sports, especially baseball, and remains active in church and community life. He can be reached at usma86@cox.net | 703-286-9398."
