    "Edited Writeup": "Gerard Curran Gerry lives in Madison, Connecticut, with his wife of 28 years. They have three children: Brendan, 26, part owner of the Madison Watch Company and a Quinnipiac graduate; Luke, 24, who works for Vanguard in Devon, Pennsylvania; and Larissa, 20, a junior at FIT in New York City. He served as an ER doctor, deploying to Afghanistan with Task Force Bagram attached to 5th Special Forces Group from November 2001 to April 2002. He has practiced at MidState Medical Center in Meriden, St. Francis Hospital in Hartford, and the VA in West Haven, Connecticut. He can be reached at gcurranlara@cshore.com | 203-694-9997."
