    "State": "NY",
    "Metro Area": "Syracuse",
    "Edited Writeup": "Howard “Howie” Curtis Howie  lives in Saratoga Springs, New York, in the very building he and his wife lived in a decade ago. His three sons have settled in Montana near Whitefish: Michael works construction in the mountains near Jefferson, Colorado; Scott served in the Navy as a P-3 crew member and now works as a defense contractor flying drones; and Joshua supports Scott's work while caring for the dogs and traveling with him. Howie was a legendary \"double-century man\" at West Point, accumulating 200 hours of punishment tours through exploits like putting a beer bottle on the Supe's windowsill, sneaking over the wall, and placing a sailboat on top of the barracks. He served in Air Defense Artillery at the Fulda Gap in Germany, then deployed to Dhahran and King Khalid Military City during Desert Storm, working in the Combined Reporting Center coordinating multinational air defense. After the Army, Howie built a successful pharmaceutical career with Bristol Myers Squibb, working in kidney transplant immunosuppressants, cardiovascular sales, and government accounts. He especially enjoyed serving as national account manager for New York and Pennsylvania, later moving to Maine and Colorado covering large territories. He enjoys skiing, hockey, and spirited travel adventures, thriving on camaraderie and spontaneous fun. He can be reached at hcurtis_148@comcast.net | 603-591-1343."
