    "Edited Writeup": "Tom lives  in Wisconsin Rapids, Wisconsin, where he is retired and enjoying camping, taking cruises around the world, and time with grandchildren. His most notable Army assignments were with 3/64 Armor in Schweinfurt, Germany and on the G3 Operations staff for 1st Cavalry Division during Desert Storm. After the Gulf War he returned to his hometown to raise a family and apply his computer science degree, spending 30 years in IT across the paper and insurance industries, including a role as VP of Application Development for Stora Enso, a global paper company, which had him shuttling monthly between Stockholm, Helsinki, and Dusseldorf before retiring in 2021. He has three sons, the eldest two nearby with five grandchildren between them, and a youngest who graduated USMA 2018 and serves as a Captain in Special Operations Civil Affairs at Fort Bragg. As an empty-nest project he earned a private pilot's license, flying his plane to the Bahamas, across the country, and to West Point to deliver Wisconsin beer during his son's cadet years. He and his wife Carol, accordion and drums respectively, perform as a duo and describe themselves as a big hit on the nursing home circuit. Tom can be reached at 715-459-6641 and tomdavis.wi@gmail.com."
