    "Edited Writeup": "Jim DiOrio lives at the Jersey Shore and is most grounded when he is close to family.Family is everything to Jim. He is the proud father of two and the grateful grandfather of two boys who keep him anchored to what matters. His daughter Jen and son-in-law Matt are raising Sal, three, and Vin, one, two little men who already define his sense of legacy. His son Jim married Anastasia on November 1, 2024, a moment Jim considers one of the great blessings of his life. He is also deeply grateful for his relationship with Kristen, whose steady presence, love, and support have brought peace, joy, and balance into his life in ways he does not take for granted. Jim stays close to his West Point Class of 1986. He golfs regularly with a wide circle of ’86ers and reconnects often at Johnny Mac events, reunions, and the informal gatherings that matter most. Right out of West Point, Jim took what he calls a surprising path that few classmates knew much about at the time. He worked in intelligence and then spent decades in the FBI as a street agent, handling difficult, complex cases and building assets where trust was earned the hard way. After retiring, he founded his own company with his lifelong best friend Anthony Boffa and trusted colleagues from the intelligence community. In 2022, during the celebration of life for Laurie Whipple, the wife of his classmate Eric, Jim began his walk with Christ. That moment changed everything. His classmate Stan Olson played a pivotal role in leading him back to God, a gift Jim carries with deep gratitude. Jim remains closely connected to his classmates and friends and is always glad to hear from them. He can be reached at jdiorio006@gmail.com  732-609-6473"
