    "Edited Writeup": "Mike Dishman Mike’s his wife lives in Texas while he's based in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. They have a 24-year-old daughter at the University of Texas. His plebe company was I1, graduating from C4. His most memorable cadet experience was serving as Sergeant of the Guard following completion of his 206th area tour.His military service took him through assignments in the US, Korea, Greece, Turkey, Lebanon, and Qatar. He found Lebanon his most interesting posting, CENTCOM his most rewarding, and Turkey the most fun and educational. After the Army, he became a defense contractor, starting with small consultancies before moving to larger defense sector companies. His most interesting role was serving as an advisor to the UAE Land Forces and the Presidential Guard—work that kept him engaged in the Middle East and connected to senior military leadership across the region. He enjoys travel, with extensive experience across the Middle East, Mediterranean, and Asia. He can be reached at dishmanm@hotmail.com."
