    "Edited Writeup": "Craig Doescher Doesch lives in Newport News, Virginia. He has two sons: one is a police officer in Northern Virginia, and the other is an Army logistician who went through ROTC at James Madison University and is currently stationed at Fort Campbell with deployments to Poland and the Middle East. He was stationed in Bamberg, Germany, during the fall of the Berlin Wall. His unit was nuclear-capable artillery, and he took visiting family into East Berlin through Checkpoint Charlie. He later served at Fort Lewis and Fort Polk and helped run warfighter training at JRTC. After serving in Germany, he earned a master's degree at the University of Central Florida and returned to West Point as a systems engineering instructor. Today, he works for a Federally Funded Research and Development Center (FFRDC) conducting war games and simulations to improve military decision-making. He remains closely connected to West Point, mentoring cadets through summer internships focused on topics like UAV swarm optimization and modern battlefield technology. His older brother Kurt is class of '83. He grew up 28 minutes from West Point. He enjoys beach days, historic sites like Jamestown and Williamsburg, and welcomes visits from classmates. He can be reached at Cdoescher64@gmail.com | 703-209-0475."
