    "Edited Writeup": "Hope lives in Tampa, Florida. She has no children and her closest family anchor is her sister and extended family in Florida, with whom she spends significant time. Her plebe company was not specified, graduating from H4. Her strongest memories include life in the Lost 50s, sponsor families who supported her, long hours on the tennis team, simple pleasures like Pebble Beach tanning on top of Arvin Gym, and covertly keeping a pet mouse in the company shoebox until the battalion NCO made her release it on the Ho Chi Minh Trail. She recalls H-4 as a good company and West Point as a place where she stayed under the radar academically and disciplinarily. She did not commission due to a sudden medical issue which shaped her early post-graduation period. Her military highlight became service adjacent: deep involvement with West Point Societies across the country, running young-grad programs in DC, and later serving on the AOG Board of Trustees. Her first role was with DARPA's contractor SPC in Washington, D.C., reached through a West Point connection. She earned an MBA and spent 10 years in financial services with Merrill Lynch and Franklin Templeton. After 9/11 she sought work with greater meaning and returned to defense contracting in Tampa. She later joined the Veterans Administration, again via a West Point connection, and now serves as a remote program manager in the VHA supply-chain program office, which she considers her most meaningful and rewarding role. She enjoys swimming, yoga, walking the Tampa Riverwalk, and attending Tampa Bay Lightning hockey and Buccaneers football games. She likes cultural events, outdoor festivals, and frequently takes weekend trips. She enjoys social gatherings with friends, including annual get-togethers with female classmates. She remains highly active in the West Point Society of West Central Florida, where she is currently secretary. She emphasizes gratitude, giving people grace, and deliberately \"stopping to smell the roses\" as key lessons from a varied life and career. She can be reached at dcdonnelly@aol.com | 813-466-9091."
