    "Edited Writeup": "Rob lives in Marina del Rey, California. He has been married to Kim for 29 years, and they've lived in 28 places during that time. He has no children, joking \"Ha! Me, kids??? I'm not responsible enough for that.\" His plebe company was D4, graduating from I3. His most memorable cadet experiences include an evening spent stuffing BG Boylan's office with newspaper, men's track and field, sailing team, serving as snow sport instructor, and tactics club (infantry). He loved being 2-60 Infantry AT Platoon leader as they helped develop the HMMWV in the Army at Fort Lewis, Washington. After the Army, he tried the cop thing for a couple of years, but it wasn't the job for him, so he started climbing mountains. He worked in the outdoor industry for quite a while—in shops, in climbing gyms, as an independent rep, as a tech rep, and as an alpine climber. He also repped a few bike companies. Now he drives boats, having started with dive boats in Hawaii and now tourist boats in Marina del Rey (up to 500 passengers). He stands in awe at what the class has accomplished, joking that he hasn't had a real job in 30-plus years and is gobsmacked at how well everyone has done. Despite being out of the Army, he still seems to move all the time. He enjoys travel, skeet and sporting clays, and cocktails. He can be reached at robdowse@me.com | 720-470-2141."
