    "Metro Area": "Charleston",
    "Edited Writeup": "Will Duke Will lives in Georgetown, South Carolina after 20+ years in Atlanta. His daughter Emily (30) graduated TCU in 2018, worked at Textron, Korn Ferry, Heidrick & Struggles, and McKinsey before earning her MBA from SMU in 2025. She now works at Texas Capital in Dallas. His son Dallas (28) graduated University of Oklahoma in 2020 and lives in Atlanta working as a salesman for Pinnacle Freight, a logistics brokerage company. His plebe company was F3, graduating from C1. His most memorable assignment was the first Gulf War. As S-3 Air, the night before the ceasefire he navigated an un-armored HMMWV across two brigades of M1 Tanks and M2 Bradleys on a moonless night without GPS to reach the Division Jump TOC. After two hours of dead reckoning and getting stuck on a berm for 90 minutes, he learned they came extremely close to being fired upon. He was carrying a portrait of Saddam Hussein from Jalibah Airfield that the battalion commander wanted to give to General Barry McCaffrey, that portrait reportedly still sits in the 24th ID museum at Fort Stewart. Following the Gulf War, he attended Duke business school and since 1993 has worked in the financing sector with private equity firms investing in healthcare. His strongest cadet memories are C-1 trips to NYC with Tony Hylton and others—including a Billy Idol concert at Nassau Coliseum where Hylton's \"brilliant idea\" to take the 59th Street bridge back to avoid tolls left them stuck for 90 minutes, and a trip to see The Romantics at a venue in Manhattan's East Village. He stopped drinking cold turkey on Labor Day 2008 with a goal for taking September off, and by grace hasn't had alcohol since. He enjoys cycling, fishing, swimming, and attending sports events. He can be reached at Rangerduke86@gmail.com | 770-315-0120."
