    "Edited Writeup": "Phyllis Erkins Phyllis lives in Opelika, Alabama. She moved south to be near her parents in Eufaula, Alabama and her daughter Ashley and son-in-law Keith in Florida. No human grandbabies yet but two beautiful dogs that she spoils when she goes to Florida. Her best memories from cadet days stem from the friendships she made as we bonded together to get through the years. She has very special memories of her roommates Julie, Patti, and Ranelle, and her bestie Valerie (Washington) Pendergrass. She could not have made it through without them. She was privileged to serve 20 years and retire. Her favorite assignments were in Germany, with her most favorite being her time as a company commander in Baumholder, the Rock. Being in Germany allowed her to travel to many different countries in a few short hours, and she would go back today. After the Army, she transitioned to civil service with the Defense Logistics Agency (DLA) as an Operations Research Analyst. She had many logistics jobs with DLA before moving to FEMA for her last year. She enjoyed her time with both agencies but had no regrets hanging up her boots to retire and move close to family. Phyllis enjoys the Chicks of 86 mini reunions and hopes to make more of them in the coming years. She loves to travel, attend concerts, and sporting events, mostly football. She can be reached at dstltclady@aol.com | 804-386-9932."
