    "Edited Writeup": "John Farley John lives in Scottsdale, Arizona. He has been married to Angela for 12 years. They have two children an eleven-year-old boy Joshua and nine-year-old girl Gianna. His plebe company was A3, graduating from D1.His most memorable cadet experiences were D1 Ducks, Company boxing and The Cadet Gospel Choir. He attended medical school at Uniformed Services University of the Health Sciences after graduation. He subsequently completed his residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology followed by a fellowship in Gynecologic Oncology at Walter Reed Army Medical Center. He served mostly in the National Capital Area with stints in Portsmouth Virginia, Honolulu Hawaii and Bagram Afghanistan. He retired from the Army and moved to Phoenix Arizona where he currently works as a Gynecologic Oncologist for Common Spirit Health and is Assistant Dean for Diversity, Inclusion and Belonging at the Creigton University School of Medicine Phoenix Campus. He enjoys his family, movies and the Diamondbacks. He can be reached at farleyjh@me.com, 240-672-2056"
