    "Edited Writeup": "Terry Finley Terry splits his time between Bowling Green, Kentucky; Hollywood, Florida; and Saratoga Springs, New York, with his wife Debbie. They have a son and a daughter and five grandchildren. After graduating from West Point in 1986, Terry served as an Army officer before transitioning into business. In 1991, he founded West Point Thoroughbreds with one partner and one claiming horse, driven by the idea that more people should have access to the excitement and camaraderie of Thoroughbred racing. Over the past three decades, he has grown the company into the largest Thoroughbred partnership organization in the world, with more than 700 partners and about 150 horses currently in training. West Point runners have earned more than 1,250 career victories and nearly $100 million in purses. The stable has campaigned top-level performers including Kentucky Derby winner Always Dreaming, Horse of the Year and Breeders’ Cup Classic champion Flightline, and 2025 Champion Two-Year-Old Filly Super Corredora. Terry earned an MBA from Boston University and later completed the Owner/President Management program at Harvard Business School. He serves as a steward of The Jockey Club, is a board member of the Kentucky Horse Racing and Gaming Corporation, chairs the New York Racetrack Chaplaincy, and is a longtime board member of the Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund. He enjoys time with family, classmates, and partners at the racetrack. He can be reached at terry@westpointtb.com | 609-636-7204"
