    "Edited Writeup": "Mike Flanagan Mike lives in Manakin Sabot, Virginia, with his high school sweetheart Melia. They have three children—Thomas (TJ), Mary, and Catherine (Kate)—and six granddaughters ranging from 1 to 17 years old, all living in Virginia. After 27 years in the Army, Mike retired from the Army in Orlando, FL (2013) and moved back to Virginia in 2015 to be closer to the granddaughters. As a Cadet, Mike’s CTLT with the 11th ACR led him to Armor for the first nine years in the Army. Mike later transitioned to the Army Acquisition Corps following grad school and served in program management and R&D assignments. His favorite assignment took him to arms shows across Europe, the Middle East, and Africa. The most rewarding job was leading the Abrams Tank System program office (2004-6) during OIF. Following retirement from the Army, Mike worked in the defense industry for CACI, LMI, and The Spectrum Group. During Mark Esper’s tenure as Secretary of the Army, Mike was one of eight to ten classmates that Mark appointed as Civilian Aides (aka CASA) for their respective states. As CASA Virginia (South) for six years, Mike reconnected with the Army and worked with several classmates that he hadn’t known at West Point. Mike has also enjoyed serving on the board of his local West Point Society, especially returning for the annual class and society leader conferences. He and Melia are interested in travel, particularly after two tours in Germany with classmates. He welcomes visitors passing through Richmond and is glad to help classmates needing connections in Virginia. He can be reached at mike.flanagan.usma86@gmail.com | 804-349-6235."
