    "Edited Writeup": "Brian and his wife Lynn live in Bolivia, NC. They have one daughter who is an occupational therapist at Franciscan Children's Hospital in Boston and is engaged to be married next August. Brian served mostly in Germany and Fort Carson.  While in Germany he served as a platoon leader and XO, but he also had the opportunity to do multinational air defense HAWK battery evaluations, working with German and other NATO team leaders.  Following his first assignment, Brian branch-transferred to the Transportation Corps and was lucky enough to meet his wife Lynn who was also attending in the TC Advanced Course at Ft. Eustis.  Luckily they had a great assignment officer who agreed to send them both to Ft. Carson.  Following his 7 years of active duty and 3 years of dating,  Brian and Lynn married and he attended the University of Tennessee to earn his MBA in Logistics & Transportation. Brian's civilian career included 2 years at CSX Transportation and then 27 years with Penske Logistics. His most interesting Penske role was as the operational leader for the Starbucks account for 8 years. Last February Brian retired and they moved from PA to NC.  He enjoys boating, hiking, travel and volunteering.  His most recent volunteer gigs are helping to teach elementary school science class and as a Team Rubicon Greyshirt (food pantry support, Habitat for Humanity builds, etc.).  He can be reached at Brian.Fues@gmail.com | 949-279-4544."
