    "Edited Writeup": "Richard Gabaldon Rich lives in Maitland, Florida. He has a blended family with five grown children and a new grandchild with another on the way in March 2026. His plebe company was C2, graduating from I4. His most memorable cadet experiences were walking the Corps prior to Sosh/Econ due dates campaigning for Class VP, being Captain of the GOAT football team, and powerlifting in the \"Animal House.\" Most of his time was with the 7th and 15th Infantry regiments at Fort Stewart, Georgia and in Germany. Serving in Desert Storm after IOAC was a unique experience at the \"Tip of the Spear.\" After the Army, he spent 20 years at Ericsson introducing digital cellular communications primarily in the Southeast and is currently looking for that next exciting role. He loves to travel and be with family and friends. He can be reached at Richgabaldon@gmail.com | 770-608-7886."
