    "State": "AZ",
    "Metro Area": "Phoenix",
    "Edited Writeup": "Eric Gaines Eric lives a digital nomad lifestyle, primarily identifying with both Florida and Arizona but traveling extensively across North America in his van. He has four adult children in their late 20s to mid-30s. One daughter lives in Florida with five children and a sixth on the way—he's currently spending extended time with that family. One son survived a severe traumatic brain and spinal injury from a work accident, underwent years of rehabilitation, returned to school, and now works in Indiana with people with physical and cognitive disabilities. He grew up near West Point in Peekskill, New York and entered the Academy late in his senior year. He flew Blackhawks in an Apache brigade at Fort Hood during a major transition period for Army aviation, serving as motor officer, platoon leader, S4, and property book officer during rapid unit activation and equipment fielding, transferring hundreds of millions of dollars of equipment to deploying units during Desert Storm preparations. He graduated as an electrical and computer engineering major, serving on battalion and regimental staff. After leaving active duty during the early 1990s drawdown, he began as an engineer with Quaker Oats in Illinois, then spent 17 years with General Electric, including time as a Six Sigma Black Belt. He later transitioned to flexible contract work, allowing partial retirement and location independence. He lost his wife to cancer after a long illness and later reinvented his life around adventure, faith, and service to family. He's deeply committed to hiking, backpacking, mountaineering, and extended travel, including solo backcountry trips in Alaska. He works only when he chooses, supported by remote connectivity, while prioritizing travel and family. Grandchildren are a major focus of his life and travel decisions. He can be reached at eagfllvn@gmail.com | 727-237-4624."
