    "Edited Writeup": "Stephen Galloway Stephen lives in Williston, Tennessee with his wife Melanie. They have triplets who have graduated from college: both daughters are in Physicians Assistant graduate programs with one daughter married, and their son is an Aerospace Engineer in Huntsville, Alabama. Stephen was a plebe in C4 and graduated from D3. He attended West Point with his twin brother David, who was in D4. He had a family-like relationship with Col Albert Rushton's home and remembers the Whiner Fests as memorable unofficial D3 events. After Fort Benning, he served his entire Army commitment in the 3/504th PIR, 82nd Airborne Division, during an active period that included deployments to Panama for Operation Just Cause and to Saudi Arabia and Iraq for Operations Desert Shield and Desert Storm. After leaving the Army, he attended NC State for veterinary school, where he met Melanie. They practiced in the Texas Panhandle for a few years before returning to Tennessee to start their current practice 25 years ago. Stephen became a specialist in dentistry and orofacial surgery, was a founder of the equine dentistry specialty, and has treated patients of numerous species including guinea pigs, rabbits, dogs, cats, horses, camels, lions, and tigers. He is still working but has retirement in sight. Stephen loves the outdoors, hunts a little, fishes a lot, and backpacks off-grid at least once a year. Fly fishing and fly tying are current obsessions. The family travels abroad as much as possible. He can be reached at achvet@yahoo.com | 901-497-2359."
