    "Metro Area": "Toronto, Canada",
    "Edited Writeup": "Michael Garcia Michael lives in Tucson, Arizona. His plebe company was D4, graduating from E2. He served with the 2nd Squadron, 3rd Armored Cavalry Regiment after Basic Armor Course. After leaving the Army, he started his civilian career as a production team leader at Kimberly-Clark making diapers in Paris, Texas. He earned his MBA from Harvard in 1999 and spent the next 25 years in heavy industry - aluminum, steel, and pulp and paper - with assignments in China, South Africa, and Canada. He served on the Board of the Federal Reserve Bank of Richmond and now serves on the Board of Alliant Energy. He officially retired at the end of 2025 after serving as President and CEO of Algoma Steel, which he describes as the most interesting role of his career - part industrial transformation, part trade-policy roller coaster, part international diplomacy, and part \"herding cats at -30°C.\" He enjoys golf, skiing, and attending sporting events. He can be reached at mdg64@mac.com | 803-322-9651."
