    "Edited Writeup": "Pat Gavin Pat lives in Lee's Summit, Missouri. He has two sons: Nick, 28, and Jack, 25. Nick and his wife Maddy have a two-month-old son named Noah. He served as battalion S-3 Air in 1st Infantry Division during Desert Storm, helping coordinate operations during the 100-hour ground campaign. His unit breached Iraqi trench lines as part of the \"Hail Mary\" maneuver and ultimately secured the Safwan airfield where surrender negotiations occurred. After returning from the Gulf War, he left active duty, married, and attended law school in Kansas City. He became an employment lawyer, first in private practice and then moving in-house. He now serves in the legal department at T-Mobile and has spent nearly three decades in the field. He grew up in Dunkirk, New York, majored in political science, and developed a deep interest in presidential studies, completing research at the Eisenhower and Roosevelt libraries. He met his wife while stationed at Fort Riley and has lived in Lee's Summit for more than 30 years. He golfs, attends sports and cultural events, throws axes, and goes wine tasting. He can be reached at PMGavin86@gmail.com | 816-210-2712."
