    "Edited Writeup": "Todd Gile TA lives in Hoosick Falls, New York. He has five children. His oldest is an Army captain serving as a recruiting company commander in Manhattan with a daughter. His second child lives in Minneapolis with two children. His third child, born at West Point, lives in Louisville with one child. He and his wife adopted a boy from Ukraine while stationed in Germany who lives with them. His youngest enlisted in the Guard and recently started basic training at Fort Leonard Wood. He highlighted operational assignments including jumping into Honduras shortly after arriving at Fort Bragg, serving during Desert Storm as part of a replacement engineer element, and later commanding in Alaska. He repeatedly emphasized satisfaction with engineer demolitions work, including large cache-destruction missions. After the Army, he worked for about 12 years with a leadership consulting firm affiliated with West Point's Thayer Hotel, supporting programs and coordinating work partly from home and partly on-site. He grew up in Appleton, Wisconsin, earned a master's in exercise science at Indiana University, returned to West Point, and ran and streamlined the boxing program after Herb Kraton's long tenure. He lives on a farmhouse in northern New York near the Vermont border, hosting classmates who visit and participate in farm chores. He can be reached at tagile82@gmail.com | 906-360-3335."
