    "Edited Writeup": "Mo lives in Haverford, Pennsylvania. She and her '78 grad husband have three adult kids. The older two are both married and living in Virginia; the younger lives with them in Philadelphia. She has one granddaughter. She spent time in the Netherlands and Baghdad. One of her most interesting assignments was as Marketing Officer in the Admissions office at West Point, working on catalogs, posters, and videotapes. She served as a nuclear-certified Lance missile officer in Holland. Her 2008–2009 deployment to Baghdad as day MOC chief in the U.S. Embassy involved monitoring Arabic and international media, coordinating messaging among State, DoD, and senior leaders, and helping stand up operations in the new embassy compound. After 27 years of active duty, she retired as a field artillery officer with public affairs as her functional area and went to a veteran-serving nonprofit. She throttled back from full-time employment to part-time roles to take care of family, worked for the Census Bureau during COVID, then in local customer-facing jobs including AAA travel services. She currently works part-time for a small insurance firm while attending part-time evening law school at Rutgers Law in Camden, New Jersey. She helps lead the class TAPS project. She loves seeing new places and watches any and all sports competitions—football, lacrosse, equestrian, Army Women's Ice Hockey. She can be reached at mo_gillen@yahoo.com | 757-602-9651."
