    "Edited Writeup": "Alyson Goermar Alyson lives in Boca Raton, Florida. Her plebe company was E3, graduating from I4. Her most memorable cadet experiences were traveling away from West Point for volleyball matches with wonderful teammates and going to her sponsor's house to chill on occasional weekends. She attended Fort Lee, Virginia (home of the Quartermaster) for OBC and QM schools, then was stationed in Germany where the Berlin Wall came down in the middle of her tour in 1989. As the 501st Support Battalion fuel platoon leader, she created and implemented the first Refuel On The Move for the 1st Armored Division, which was groundbreaking at the time. After the Army, she worked in process improvement and quality control. She was a Lead Examiner for the Florida Sterling Council where her team examined public and private organizations based on National Malcolm Baldrige business excellence practices, working as an efficiency expert and management consultant. Her current hobby is wildlife and landscape photography. She loves to travel, with Normandy as a winner destination. She can be reached at AlysonGoermar@gmail.com | 561-767-0284."
