    "Edited Writeup": "Dennis Greenwood Dennis lives in McCordsville, Indiana with his wife Carol Genseal. They have two daughters—Sarah in Lincoln, Nebraska and Shannon in San Francisco. He retired as a Lieutenant Colonel in June 2006 from the Pentagon where he served on the OSD SOLIC staff. His career as a Military Police Officer and in special operations emphasized Civil Affairs and antiterrorism, taking him through Fort McClellan twice, Fort Riley, Grafenwoehr and Vilseck in Germany, Fort Benjamin-Harrison, Fort Leavenworth, Fort Bragg twice, Bosnia, and Saudi Arabia. His most notable assignments came as the ARCENT liaison to the Saudi military immediately after the Khobar bombing and as an antiterrorism action officer in the Pentagon after 9/11. After active duty he worked for Northrop Grumman as an analyst supporting the J-8 Joint Staff, then became a DoD civilian in the same role with the Warfighting Analysis Division until retiring in December 2025. During Beast he remembers Tim Knight volunteering without hesitation to help deliver the heavy Sunday New York Times papers—when Knight became First Captain, Greenwood thought it well deserved. Now retired, he travels and looks forward to more once Carol retires in a couple of years. He can be reached at dengrnwood@verizon.net | 571-237-9151."
