    "Edited Writeup": "Tater Haislop Tater lives in Seneca, South Carolina. He has one daughter, Carmen, age twenty-one, who lives locally. She is high-functioning autistic, very outgoing, and central to his daily life. He speaks of her with pride and humor, describing their close relationship and frequent shared adventures. His wife Nancy. His plebe company was F3. His nickname \"Tater\" came when Steve Cummings declared he looked like Mr. Potato Head after seeing his shaved head and acne. He remembers the 150-pound football lifestyle of extreme weight cuts, and wild team trips where he and Ted Johnston once emptied a fire extinguisher in a hotel. Ranger School was a major shared hardship with classmates. His biggest highlight was completing the Venezuelan Ranger Course, earning the nickname \"Oso Polar,\" enduring live-fire training, swamp survival, and a divided class of Marxist and pro-U.S. officers that reflected regional tensions. He later served in Panama, Honduras, and Tiger Island, calling the real-world missions some of his best experiences. He left during the drawdown seeking a new direction. A move to California and a placement by classmate Scott Poirier launched him into chemical sales in Silicon Valley. He shifted into financial services with Dean Witter during the Netscape IPO era, building a career in a notoriously high-attrition field. After many roles, he now works independently within a mutual company, focusing on tax abatement and insurance, running his own practice, and traveling frequently to clients. He sees this decade as the window for Class of '86 to deepen its connections and is committed to helping make that happen. He can be reached at thaislop@aol.com | 864-324-4455."
