    "Edited Writeup": "Marc D. Harris Marc lives in Moseley, Virginia and has five children: his 29-year-old son teaches in Connecticut, his 18-year-old daughter attends Hampton University, his 16-year-old daughter is in high school, his 11-year-old son is in middle school, and his 8-year-old daughter is in elementary school.  Marc's plebe company was D1, graduating from E4. Marc commissioned into the Signal Corps.  A highlight of his career was serving as a Presidential Communications Officer at the White House during the September 11, 2001 attacks. Following his military service, he transitioned to corporate America, working at Amazon before starting his own company. His favorite role, however, was as a stay-at-home dad. These days Marc makes an annual pilgrimage to Disney and never gets bored. His favorite West Point memory involves the time Roger Knowles predicted 8 out of 10 TEE questions, and Chris Cole (along with all the other HPA cadets in the company) used his copy of Roger's crib notes to pass his exam after his calculator ran out, receiving max partial credit by copying the crib notes onto the TEE (wrong numbers and all). Marc reflects that the amount of talent and intelligence at the Academy was and remains truly remarkable. He can be reached at marc_d_harris@post.harvard.edu | 407-670-5794"
