    "Edited Writeup": "Patti (Medina) Harris Patti lives in Florida's panhandle on a large rural property with her husband, focused on land stewardship and self-directed projects. She and her husband chose to leave the Army before starting a family, driven by a firm decision not to raise children while subject to deployments. She has two grown, independent sons, one born in Sydney, Australia during an expatriate assignment. Her plebe company was D3, graduating from C2. Her standout cadet memory is a Beast Barracks incident when her roommate Lisa Studa Baker accidentally drank from a cup containing contact lenses, temporarily leaving her unable to see. She served as a Signal Corps officer in Korea in a highly sensitive artillery detachment with a nuclear mission, managing top-secret communications materials and vaults as a junior lieutenant. She deployed with the 101st Airborne Division during Desert Storm as executive officer and logistics lead, including running a Thanksgiving mess operation in theater. After leaving active duty, she completed a master's degree in engineering technology and spent years overseas as an expatriate spouse in Australia, Thailand, and the Philippines before reentering the workforce as a science and engineering teacher. She later joined the University of Florida as part of an inaugural engineering extension and innovation office, coordinating workforce development, industry outreach, and K-12 engineering recruitment before retiring early. She and her husband now manage multiple real-estate holdings. She enjoys travel, especially meaningful travel tied to history and place shaped by years living overseas, cruises, road trips, and low-stress gatherings with classmates. She can be reached at pattijcw@yahoo.com | 941-735-9042."
