    "Edited Writeup": "Mick is married to Rhonda and is proud to be a father and grandfather. He has three adult children: Brittiney, 28, a registered nurse; Michael, 26, working in the medical device industry; and his stepson Max, 27, an Army engineer lieutenant currently stationed at Fort Stewart, GA, and soon relocating to Fort Shafter, Hawaii. Max is recently engaged to Alyssa, with plans to marry next year. Mick’s granddaughter, Blair, is 18 months old and lives nearby in Tampa with Brittiney, making family a central part of his life. A recruited football player at West Point, Mick transitioned from varsity to sprint football, playing linebacker, while concentrating in European Studies with a focus on German. His cadet memories center on company life in H2, sprint football, and close friendships. Among defining moments was surviving a shrapnel wound from a live grenade during a CTLT rotation in Berlin, though he also fondly recalls lighter memories, including a runaway classmate’s car and the tradition of “promoting” his father at cadet gatherings. A career highlight was serving in the Berlin Brigade during the fall of the Berlin Wall. Mick served 22 years on active duty, including five years with the 75th Ranger Regiment, where he commanded the Regimental Reconnaissance Detachment, and tours in South Korea, Fort Bragg, NC, Fort Drum, NY, Fort Benning, GA, and Afghanistan. Prior to retirement, he served as Professor of Military Science at Florida Southern College. After leaving active duty, he transitioned to defense work and has spent roughly 16 years as a civilian planner and strategist within U.S. Special Operations Command, holding multiple senior planning and operations roles. He enjoys golf, working out, spending time with Rhonda and family, and is an active Tampa Bay sports fan, holding season tickets for the Buccaneers. Mick remains professionally fulfilled, continues contributing at SOCOM, and emphasizes the importance of staying connected with classmates, an area he wishes he had prioritized earlier. He can be reached at mickhaydak@aol.com."
