    "Edited Writeup": "Mike Higginbottom Mike and his wife Cathy live in Leavenworth, Kansas, approaching their 40th anniversary. They have two sons. Patrick was born in 1987 at Fort Carson, graduated from West Point in 2010, and served six years as a field artillery officer including a deployment to Kandahar Province with 1/25 IN (Stryker). He's now an ICU nurse in Leavenworth. Brendan was born in 1992 at Fort Bliss, graduated from the University of Kansas and UC Davis, and lives in Minneapolis. Mike served 28 years in armor and cavalry positions with the 4th and 24th Infantry Divisions, 1st and 2nd Armored Divisions, and 3rd Armored Cavalry Regiment, plus staff and advisory assignments with TRADOC, Multi-National Security Transition Command-Iraq, and US Army Europe. He deployed to the Middle East with 3rd ACR during Desert Shield/Storm and Operation Intrinsic Action, to Macedonia/Kosovo with 1st AD during KFOR, and to Baghdad with MNSTC-I. He and Cathy were stationed at 18 different posts across the US and Germany. When the Army reassigned him to Fort Leavenworth in 2011 following a tour as Chief of Staff, 7th Army Training Command in Grafenwoehr, they bought a home in the city and Cathy declared she wasn't moving again. His final position was TRADOC Capability Manager-Mission Command, retiring as a colonel on July 1, 2014. After retirement he worked as a military analyst with Booz Allen before being hired by the Department of the Army in 2016 as a supervisory training analyst with the Combined Arms Center-Training. He retired from federal service October 1, 2025. Mike rides and cleans his motorcycles, reads, and tries to stay calm watching the national news. Cathy reads, gardens, and rides as a passenger with Mike. Both do strength training, biking, walking, and yoga. To celebrate their 40th anniversary, they're traveling to Vienna in July for several days before linking up with a motorcycle tour group in Bratislava for a 10-day ride across multiple countries. He can be reached at mike.higginbottom@hotmail.com | 913-702-6947."
