    "Edited Writeup": "Ted Hoyt Ted lives in Hopkinton, Massachusetts. He is married with three children and no grandchildren yet. His daughter Ellora graduated in 2025 from UMass Amherst Honors College with a dual major in Microbiology and Organic Chemistry and currently works as a tech marketing consultant. His son Jack is a junior at Norwich University in Vermont studying geology and is in the Corps of Cadets but has not contracted with the military yet. His son Ryan is a freshman at Roger Williams University studying criminal justice. Ted remembers Wayne Locklin saving him from beatings and swirlies at the hands of the cows. During his Army service, he was sent twice for a month at a time to Russia as OIC when the Soviet Union was collapsing, he doesn't remember or won't tell much about those trips, but he did receive a letter of reprimand to help him remember. After the Army, he spent a year riding a Harley until drawdown money was gone, then went to law school courtesy of the VA and now practices law. He can be reached at jhoyt@hoytlegalllc.com."
