    "Edited Writeup": "Jim and his wife Joan live in Peterborough, New Hampshire. Their son Joey is hoping to join the West Point Class of '27, and their daughter Ellie is at Hofstra, Class of '28. Jim served twice with the 82nd Airborne Field Artillery, jumping out of planes and enjoying the crazy pace. He also served in Germany. He got out in '93 and started in medical sales, rising through management ranks before starting several medical home service and billing companies. He sold three of the four companies. The most interesting was a post-op ortho service company where he navigated billing denials effectively, took care of his employees well, and got bought out when he wanted to retire by the company he started. Neil Costello was his President and COO, now CEO. Darryl MacDonald worked in sales with them for six years. Tony Guzzi's son, now Dr. John Guzzi, worked as a service rep during his undergrad. Jim remembers Ring Weekend get-togethers, all the home football games, and trying to study for finals, usually with Darryl MacDonald. He plays golf, travels, attends sporting events, and gets together for dinners. He can be reached at jhradecky86@gmail.com | 603-540-6564."
