    "Edited Writeup": "Terry James resides in Holly Springs, North Carolina, where he works in sales. Contact information includes 919-609-9759 and tmjames86@gmail.com. He described himself as a cadet as “a regular guy that loves God, family, and country,” and his cadet highlight was walking on and earning a place on the Army baseball team, reflecting persistence and commitment. His most significant Army assignments included serving as an AOC at Fort Knox and with 3/37 Armor Battalion at Fort Riley from 1986 to 1991, roles notable for line-unit responsibility and operational tempo during his early officer years. After military service, he transitioned into a civilian sales career, where he has continued professionally to the present. His current interests include golf and attending sporting events, with particular enthusiasm for baseball and college football. Terry and his wife Susan are currently living in Myrtle Beach, SC and have two sons."
