    "Edited Writeup": "Jimmy lives in Madison, Alabama. His four children include Hunter (USMA 2013), a former Blackhawk MEDEVAC pilot in Afghanistan who now runs an Amazon Distribution Center in Huntsville with three boys; Michael (USMA 2016), a former Combat Engineer/Ranger who finished his MBA and AI Masters at Kellogg/Northwestern and lives in Newman, Georgia with three girls; Katelyn, a mechanical engineer with Exxon in Houston; and John, a Harvard economics graduate and linebacker who works as an investment banker with Founders Bank in Birmingham and is engaged to Megan Benedict, whose father Leith is a career Signal Officer around their year group. He served almost 28 years as an Air Defender in all weapon systems, including tours as an ORSA and in Space billets. The highlight was commanding a brigade downrange with most of the AD in the Middle East. After leaving the Army—the hardest decision he'd ever made—he started with Northrup Grumman for five years, moved to Dynetics for a couple years through their acquisition, then became President of a Private Equity-backed company called BlueHalo, which was recently bought by AeroVironment where he continues leading a large group. He grew up in South Carolina and had never been north of North Carolina until West Point. Many H1 classmates visited his home and skied with them during summers. He golfs, hunts, fishes, water and snow skis, and gets together often with H1 Hawgs. He can be reached at Jenkinsjimmy9@gmail.com | 915-525-5473."
