    "Town": "Clermont",
    "State": "FL",
    "Metro Area": "Orlando",
    "Edited Writeup": "Royce lives in Clermont, Florida. He has three sons: his eldest graduated USAFA '14, is a Space Force Major married to an Air Force Doctor, currently stationed at Wright-Patterson AFB in Dayton, Ohio, and they have a three-year-old granddaughter Elizabeth. His second son graduated MIT '15, was a submarine officer for 10 years and now works as an engineer for the government at Fort Meade, Maryland, married to an MIT classmate and living in Columbia, Maryland. His third son graduated MIT '16, is a mechanical engineer at an architectural lighting company, married to an MIT classmate and living in Littleton, Colorado outside Denver. His plebe company was H2, graduating from H4. H-4's spirit missions stand out for him. He credits Jim Yentz for planning and ingenuity in orchestrating missions involving the I-4 I-beam, including placing it on the pump station in Lusk reservoir using a borrowed sailboat, partnering with the Scuba Club made up of G-4 Guppies to recover it, and placing it in the Olympic pool diving well where he served as Water Safety Officer. Another fondly remembered spirit mission involved rewiring the class lights in Washington Hall, reversing the order they illuminated so after announcements the fourth class light came on first and all the plebes departed. He commissioned Transportation Corps and selected Fort Story, Virginia (Virginia Beach) as a Hovercraft Platoon Leader, getting to wear a flight suit. He PCS'd to Fort Bragg in 1989 by way of Airborne School but nearly died during Tower Week so spent his tour at Bragg as a leg. He deployed to Saudi Arabia for Desert Shield and Desert Storm, managing approximately 1,200 trucks supporting XVIII Airborne Corps. After the Army, he spent 19 years at Schneider National Carriers leading drivers and supporting dedicated customers primarily in the automotive sector, then 11 years at Amazon working in Fulfillment as Site Leader opening a new building. He's currently working as a Supply Chain Leader at a Frito Lay plant. He and his wife enjoy tubing, snorkeling, swimming, and kayaking in the many springs in central Florida. He enjoys pickleball, skiing, college football, and Pokemon Go. Being a local Disney fan, they enjoy making short trips to do just a bit at a time and people watch. He can be reached at Royce.johnson5@gmail.com | 920-227-8501."
