    "Edited Writeup": "Barry Kellar Barry lives in Clarksville, Tennessee. He is still married to his high school sweetheart Allison. They have no children but have dogs, cats, nephews, and nieces—they like the dogs more. Barry was a plebe in B3 and graduated from A4. He remembers Fred Manzo holding a hat outside the barracks 6th floor window, threatening Wayne Locklin he would drop the hat if Wayne took one more step toward him. Wayne did, the hat was dropped. Wayne informed Fred it was Pete Kuring's hat. He served at Fort Stewart with the 24th Mechanized Infantry Division and briefed General Schwarzkopf. After the Army, he worked at GE for 10 years, with his last position running a global team for GE Plastics as global director. He then moved to filtration with Freudenberg (German HQ entity) as CEO North America and global VP, retiring in 2022. He came out of retirement as CEO for HOMAG Americas, which he considers his best role—great industry and customers in the wood industry with a great company. Barry enjoys travel, scuba, sporting events, and golf if he drives the cart. He can be reached at barrykellar1@gmail.com | 270-348-2916."
