    "Edited Writeup": "Rick (“Gus”) lives in Tallmadge, Ohio. He's married to Sherry and has two married daughters, Sophia and Emma, each with one child—grandchildren Reagan Jane Lowery (26 months) and Oliver Douglas Skrapics (3 weeks). His plebe company was I4, graduating from C1. He served in the Infantry and Special Forces including two years on an SF A-Team (ODA-SCUBA). He retired in 2014 having served his final 14 years in a JSOC Special Mission Unit. His most vivid cadet memory is being on the Apron for the longest July 4th celebration, thinking \"OMG, does every state have a flower, bird, and motto?\" After the Army, he became CEO of a philanthropic grantmaker based in Ohio. He's more \"user friendly\" now and still rides a Harley. His activities focus on sport and socializing, viewing activities as the medium to connect with the many friends he wonders if he deserves. He can be reached at rkellar@pegsfoundation.org | 330-283-1086."
