    "Edited Writeup": "Paul Kelley PK lives on Mercer Island, Washington. He has two adult children living near him in the Seattle area. His 25-year-old son works in human resources as a benefits specialist, and his 23-year-old daughter is a communications manager for a nonprofit. His military highlight was jumping into Panama as a rifle platoon leader with the 2nd Ranger Battalion. Later, in civil affairs with the 96th CA Battalion, he supported missions in the Pacific, including one on Wake Island managing the return of Chinese migrants. He retired from the Army in 2006 as a lieutenant colonel—the first in the class to do so by date—and immediately joined Boeing as a strategy analyst on the defense side. His work focused on Army programs like the Future Combat Systems. He hails from Quincy, Massachusetts, and was inspired to attend West Point after a neighborhood connection to future Army Chief of Staff Jim McConville. He studied Math, Science & Engineering. He enjoys rugby reminiscing, sports events, and travel. He can be reached at pknwb3@hotmail.com | 425-577-2257."
