    "Metro Area": "WashingtonDC",
    "Edited Writeup": "Flip lives in Bristow, Virginia. His oldest son Andrew graduated from Virginia Tech in 2017 with a Chemical Engineering degree, worked as a craft brewer in Massachusetts, and now works as a water quality engineer for the state of Maryland. He's been with his girlfriend, also a 2017 Virginia Tech grad, since graduation. His youngest son Dean enlisted in the Army, received an appointment to West Point through the enlisted ranks, and graduated with the Class of 2022. Dean is an FA officer who served with the 82nd Airborne and is currently attending his CCC at Fort Sill before his next duty station at Fort Carson with the 4th Multi-Domain Task Force. Flip started as an FA officer with the 82nd Airborne Division, then served with 2/20 FA BN in Hanau, Germany as BN FDO and A Battery Commander. After the first drawdown, he transferred to 1st Armored Division working in DivArty FS. He returned to West Point to teach in the EE&CS department after getting his Masters in Computer Engineering at NC State. He served as an exchange officer with the British Army in the Royal Artillery C3I Systems Group, then worked in the Pentagon's Army G-1 Personnel Transformation Office as Chief Technology Officer and Chief of the Networks Branch for PERSINSD. After 20 years, he retired and briefly joined Booz Allen Hamilton before returning to government service as a Computer Engineer with the FBI. He worked various big data programs, eventually becoming Unit Chief of several units including the Operational Networks and Technology Unit, which ran network and data systems for digital evidence across all 50 states, and the Machining and Prototyping Unit, which he describes as basically \"Q\" from the James Bond movies. He fully retired in December 2023 after over 17 years with the FBI. His wife Linda retired from teaching in 2025. Flip skis, travels, and attends football and hockey games. He plays golf, joking that his handicap is that he plays golf. He met his wife Linda at the first time Army played in post-season football, the Cherry Bowl in Detroit. He can be reached at flip.kleinfelder@gmail.com | 571-239-2349."
