    "Edited Writeup": "Robert Kleinhample Bob lives in Williamsburg, Virginia. He has two children: Sarah, who lives in Chicago, and Julia, who lives in San Diego. His plebe company was E4, graduating from D3. His most interesting assignment was his first, the 7th Infantry Division in Monterey, California. They deployed to remove Noriega during Operation Just Cause. They trained hard and lived in a beautiful place to enjoy time off. His wife Rebecca also worked at Pebble Beach, so he was able to golf often there. He retired from the Army in 2006, and his last job was managing Army modeling and simulation for experimentation. He then joined SAIC and continued the modeling and simulation career. He continues in this career today as a consultant helping companies grow in the modeling and simulation market. He enjoys golf and follows the resurgence of Army football. He can be reached at bob.kleinhample@gmail.com | 757-325-0014."
