    "State": "OH",
    "Metro Area": "Akron",
    "Edited Writeup": "Tim Knight Tim lives in Fairlawn, Ohio, with his wife Pam in the same home for nearly 30 years. He has two adult children, both married, and is now a grandfather. His family is centered in Northeast Ohio. A major highlight was being selected as First Captain, a formative leadership experience requiring him to lead classmates while maintaining trust and credibility. He earned a Marshall Scholarship and studied at Oxford, followed by operational service in Korea with 2nd Infantry Division engineers and deployment to Desert Shield and Desert Storm with the 20th Engineer Brigade supporting XVIII Airborne Corps. After leaving active duty during the post-Desert Storm drawdown, he entered Procter & Gamble's management training program, then moved into product management at Rubbermaid. He spent 22 years at Sherwin-Williams, rising to senior leadership roles including global business president and leading mergers and acquisitions, culminating in the $11.3B Valspar acquisition. For the past nine years, he has worked as an independent consultant focused on private equity, M&A, and board service with lower- and middle-market firms. He's from Massillon, Ohio, and majored in electrical engineering at West Point. He values reunions and informal reconnections with classmates. He can be reached at taknight64@icloud.com | 216-272-8911."
