    "Metro Area": "WashingtonDC",
    "Edited Writeup": "Reinhard Koenig Rhino lives in Fairfax Station, Virginia, with his wife Melissa and their two children—a teenage daughter around 15 and a son around 11. He stepped back from professional advancement to be present for his children's activities, particularly his son's baseball games. He served more than 30 years as an Army engineer officer, with early assignments in Germany with VII Corps and deployments related to Desert Storm. He held company and battalion command at Fort Leonard Wood, senior engineer leadership roles in Iraq reconstruction, and brigade-level command in Alaska, along with multiple Pentagon assignments. He retired as a colonel in 2016. After active duty, he transitioned to federal civilian service with the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, rising to the Senior Executive Service with major assignments including New York City. He retired from civilian service about seven months ago. He grew up in rural Northern California near Happy Camp with classmate Dan Hokenson, attending Oregon State for a year before West Point. He met his wife in an immigration line in Beijing; she later became a JAG officer. During Beast Barracks, he and Hokenson developed a private \"bull drawing\" code they used to communicate. He values informal connection with classmates and enjoys international travel with his wife. His current time centers on family life, youth sports, travel planning, and maintaining friendships with classmates. He can be reached at rwkoenig1@yahoo.com | 703-901-3639."
