    "State": "SC",
    "Metro Area": "Charleston",
    "Edited Writeup": "PLAF lives in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina with his wife of 26 years, Colleen. He has one son, Luke (33) who is a mechanical engineer working in the defense industry. His cadet memories are adopting the \"Moo Baba\" persona through exaggerated exploration of martial arts, Zen, and meditation. He loved both is plebe company (C4) and the Polar Bears. Mostly he used humor as a way to offset the Academy grind. He branched Military Intelligence, and his Army highlight was deploying to Desert Storm where he was a Battalion S4 then ran night operations in the 24th Infantry Division G2. After leaving the Army, he had a varied civilian career, including early internet startups, executive roles at larger companies like Ticketmaster and Disney. He had a ten year stint living in London and Helsinki acquiring and running company units. He also took roles at companies in the US specializing in renewable energy, fitness and internet gaming. When he retired he went to India for an extended meditation retreat, visited the Muktananda Ashram, and from its grounds texted Darren Moore. The cycle was complete. He hasn’t touched the stuff since. In retirement, he focuses on maintaining class relationships, designing wargames, producing military history content online, and prioritizing people over collecting things. He enjoys battlefield tours, travel, shared meals, reunions, informal gatherings, skiing trips, and simply spending time talking and laughing with classmates. Experiences and relationships consistently take priority over structured hobbies or competitive sports. He can be reached at paul@paulklafontaine.com | 720-537-6400."
