    "Edited Writeup": "James Larsen lives in Granbury, Texas. His son Jake works as an attorney in Fort Worth with his wife Hillary and daughter McKay, with a grandson on the way. His daughter Grace works in marketing and communications for a commercial real estate company in Austin with her husband Foster. Jay served as a career aviator with assignments in Korea, Germany, Hawaii, Okinawa, and CONUS. His most interesting assignment was in Okinawa, Japan, as an amphibious planner for US 7th Fleet, where as the only Army member of the organization he developed a \"Soldier of the Quarter\" program and won easily every quarter. His terminal Colonel assignment was with US Army North at Fort Sam Houston as Chief of Training & Exercises. After retirement, he transitioned to contractor work supporting Homeland Defense training and exercises for Army North, later becoming a DA Civilian in the same organization. His most interesting post-retirement role was Chief of the Urban Search & Rescue training team. Jay skis with his H-1 brothers, attends reunions, and travels to sporting events. He's been married since 1991. He can be reached at jay_larsen@hotmail.com | 210-289-0138."
