    "Edited Writeup": "Kevin Lauterjung Kevin  lives in Akron, Ohio. He and his wife Sally have three kids in their 20s, all living in New York: Ellen practices law in Albany and is married to her Ohio State sweetheart Chris; Luke lives in Brooklyn working in marketing for pet insurance company Pumpkin; and John is finishing college at RPI in Troy. His plebe company was E2, graduating from C1. He served, worked, and played with an amazing group of lieutenants in the 9th Combat Engineer Battalion in Aschaffenburg, Germany, including Rhino Koenig and Don Johantges. They took ski trips to the Alps every Thanksgiving, played a memorable tackle football game against the armor battalion officers, and trained with our sister Panzer Battalion in Fulda.  His most memorable cadet experience was a trip to NYC with about eight Chargin' Charlie classmates, doing a Billy Idol concert, and staying with Tony Hylton's parents in Queens. After the Army, he worked in health care consulting, then spent 15 years at a health insurance company culminating as EVP of Managed Care. He started an energy brokerage in 2013 and an energy services company in 2021, remaining active with both while dabbling in real estate and commercial property development. Sally and their two oldest kids are all Ohio State graduates. The family holds season tickets and follows Buckeyes football closely. He's an Army football fan who particularly enjoys tailgating. He can be reached at sklauterjung@gmail.com | 330-607-2829."
