    "Metro Area": "Tacoma",
    "Edited Writeup": "Karen “Kat” Lee (Turner)  lives in Des Moines, Washington. She and her husband Alan Ellison have five children combined and eight grandchildren. Her son Marshall is completing his degree in molecular biology and wants to teach and research. Her daughter Mariah is a professional soccer player who will retire either this year or next year to attend NYU Law School. Her stepdaughter is a lawyer with six kids. Her stepgrandson Tyce is graduating from SDSU this year and will work for an engineering firm. She was stationed in Germany in the 1980s and was able to take a team to participate in the annual Nijmegan International March. She practiced law for a few years, then spent her middle management years at Puget Sound Energy, an electric and gas utility based in Bellevue, Washington. She served on the Governor's Cabinet and as an Agency Director in the Gregoire Administration, then was CEO of Pioneer Human Services, a social enterprise aerospace manufacturing company that hires people coming out of prison. She's now CEO of Plymouth Housing, the region's largest provider of Permanent Supportive Housing, serving close to 4,000 formerly homeless people annually. Her father was the first African American General Officer in the Army Medical Corps. Her plebe company was G1, graduating from G3. She and her husband powerboat and keep a 59-foot yacht in downtown Seattle. She's working on her golf game and plays soccer once a week in a women's league. She's interested in writing a book about her father's career and enjoys genealogy. She hosted the Chicks of '86 in Seattle this past year. She can be reached at ktl1986@msn.com | 206-510-0504."
