    "State": "SC",
    "Metro Area": "Greenville SC",
    "Edited Writeup": "Michael Lee Mike lives in Greenville, South Carolina. He met Andrea (Andy) during his first duty station assignment at Fort Hood. His oldest, Lauren, lives in Greenville, South Carolina - a Desert Storm baby who was a teacher but stays at home raising their three grandchildren (currently 5, 3, and 3 months) and helps her husband in home building. His second, Stephen, is married and is a civil engineer in Raleigh, North Carolina. His youngest, Andrew, also married, is in Charlotte and works for Ally Bank. Mike has many great memories of the Glee Club and the trips they took - including possibly renting a car in Hawaii, pulling into a beach parking lot, opening the back and having empty beer cans roll out clattering. He walked the area only once because he, Cabes, and Rooner returned from Spring Break minutes late for formation from skiing in Utah. Between Cow year and Firstie year, he and Hoke drove from New York to California, then picked up Cabes in Utah for the drive back to West Point and fried the CB radios in a lightning storm in South Dakota. He also remembers going home with Corsi to Dover, Ohio at Thanksgiving and playing the annual Turkey Bowl. On that trip he realized he did have a \"friend in Pennsylvania\" (highway patrol). He commissioned as a Signal officer and served in many types of units. As part of 2nd Armored Division, he deployed to Desert Storm with the Tiger Brigade attached to the 1st Marine Division. He was then stationed at Bragg where he did company command in the 82nd Airborne Division followed by a stint in a Special Mission Unit at Bragg - his most memorable times but he can't talk about them. He served in Germany with 1st Armored Division, then had an ROTC assignment in Boston as an APMS at MIT and as the PMS at Boston University. He retired after 22 years of service.  After retiring from the Army, he spent 17 years in banking as a consultant, retiring in December 2025. Mike has enjoyed getting together with classmates for sporting events over the years and hopes to do more of it in the coming years. He can be reached at mjlee71647@gmail.com | 910-508-9993."
