    "Edited Writeup": "Mike Lemanski resides in Davidsonville, Maryland, where he continues to work within the Department of Defense as he approaches retirement. Contact information includes 443-370-8404 and lemampebk@yahoo.com. He described his cadet experience with understatement, noting graduation itself as a highlight. He also spent considerable time skiing the West Point ski slope to get away and spent time with the G1 group. His most significant Army service included six years in Stuttgart, Germany serving first as a lieutenant and later returning as a major and lieutenant colonel. Mike taught in the EECS Department at West Point and commanded a company in the United Kingdom. After military service, he remained in Department of Defense–related work, continuing a long association with defense missions and institutions, and at time of writing is preparing for retirement. His current interests center heavily on skiing, travel, attending sporting events, and hiking. Mike and his wife Pam have two daughters living in Cleveland, a son in Colorado Springs, two grandchildren, and a son-in-law.zTBD"
