    "Edited Writeup": "David Ley David lives in Trophy Club, Texas with his wife Julia, who hails from Nottingham, England—they married in November 2019. He has three daughters: two live locally (one married, one not), and one lives single in Orlando, Florida. His middle daughter in Orlando has a side gig as a professional wrestler. Julia is the \"cruise queen\" who loves cruising. His plebe company was A1, graduating from C3. He served from 1986-1991, completing Airborne School at Benning, Armor Officer Basic at Knox, then 5/77 Armor in Mannheim, Germany, Armor Officer Advanced at Knox, and Bradley NETT-T assignments at Knox, Benning, Polk, and Hood. His funniest cadet memory is probably his \"discovery of Ash Wednesday.\" After the Army, he worked primarily in commercial and government construction management and IT project management. He did a 6-month tour as logistics manager at McMurdo Station, Antarctica with Bill Woodring. His private sector construction work was primarily at Disney and Universal in Orlando. His public sector work included facility management and construction with the VA in Orlando and USACE at Bliss, Hood, San Antonio, and Kandahar (18-month tour), then IT project management at Treasury. He was a foster parent for 6 years in Florida. He's Christian and enjoys golf, skeet shooting, travel, local sport events, and cruises. He ballroom dances with Julia. He can be reached at dj_ley@hotmail.com | 817-881-2888."
