    "Edited Writeup": "Elizabeth Lind Liz lives in Ann Arbor, Michigan. Her son Jonathan, 24, is a lovely person and an early childhood educator. He lives right around the corner from her and she sees him frequently. Liz remembers on R-day that she and her beast roommate, Caroline Keller, thought it was oddly thoughtful of the academy to provide them with shower caps, which were in fact their hat rain covers. A very relevant highlight was being assigned to West Point for 12 years as a Reservist to teach MA206, Probability and Statistics, in STAP. It was nice to come back with perspective and gratitude for her alma mater. After the Army, she has mostly worked in Information Technology in a variety of roles. She is currently at the University of Michigan getting set for one more big project before she retires. Liz has extreme fatigue with long COVID and likely will not attend the reunion. She can be reached at liz.lind@comcast.net | 734-904-5123."
