    "Edited Writeup": "Jim Marshall Jim lives in Miramar, Florida. He has three children: John, 25, who is autistic and lives with him; Lee, 22, who is graduating from the University of Central Florida with a degree in computer science and will be commissioned as a 2LT in Cyber branch, detailed to Armor; and Ashley, 19, who is also at UCF in Army ROTC, did a semester abroad in the UK, earned the Norwegian Foot March Badge, and is doing an internship with Lockheed Martin. As a cadet in C1, he roomed with Kevin Lauterjung, an unlikely pairing between a farm boy from Illinois and a guy from LA. That turned into a close friendship, including a cross-country road trip to California. Jim served as a Cavalry Officer in storied units including the 3rd Armored Division and the 3rd and 11th Armored Cavalry Regiments, deploying for Desert Shield and Desert Storm. He completed 33 rotations at the National Training Center, 3 as a unit, 20 with the Operations Group, and 10 with OPFOR. He later served as a Public Affairs Officer with a tour in Kosovo, travel throughout South America and Guantanamo, and earned a master's degree in Mass Communication from UNC Chapel Hill. He retired as a Colonel in 2010 after serving as Director of Public Affairs at U.S. Southern Command. After retirement, Jim worked as communications director for the FBI's Miami Field Office, enjoying the people and mission enough to stay longer than planned. Jim enjoys traveling, fishing, sport shooting, hiking, and researching and conducting battlefield terrain rides. He has taken his children on vacations to at least 41 states including Alaska twice. In summer 2027, he and Army buddies from his Germany LT days plan to follow the WWII battle route of the 3rd Armored Division across France, Belgium, and Germany while podcasting. He can be reached at jimz07@yahoo.com | 910-263-1229."
