    "Edited Writeup": "Rich is a visionary leader known for leaping tall… Oh, wait! This isn’t LinkedIn. Sorry. Rich is a man of many names; Richard if you knew him in up through high school, Willis if you knew him at West Point, and Rich if you’ve known him since. Rich has lived outside of Huntsville, Alabama since leaving the Army in 1991. He has been happily married 39 years to his high school sweetheart, Annette. They have three children who all graduated at least once from the University of Alabama (ROLL TIDE): Brittney (37), married to Ryan; Courtney (34), married to Chase; and Trey (32), married to Toby. Brittney and Ryan have three children—Reagan (11), Everett (10), and Riley (8). Trey and Toby have Marie, who’s 17 months old. Rich was a Gopher (G3) as a plebe, graduating from the Happy Company (H2) where his best friends to this day come from. His most memorable cadet experiences were the Happy Two Beach Parties they held the week before spring break, and the joy of walking 61 hours on the area during graduation week. Rich was a tread head (tanker) in the Army (1-64 AR) and deployed to Desert Storm with the 24th Infantry Division. Alerted a week after he and Annette found out they were expecting their second child and returning five days before Courtney was born, he likes to tease Annette (from out-of-arms reach) that it was the perfect pregnancy, where he was there for conception and birth, and nothing in between! ;-) After Desert Storm, he got out and did 9 years in the healthcare industry before spending the next 26 in the defense industry. He’s had the opportunity to run three different small businesses as well as some P&L organizations in publicly traded Fortune 500 organizations. His most satisfying job is his current one where he works as a Deputy GM with classmate Jimmy Jenkins at AV, a defense technology company (AVAV). He believes their business group has some of the coolest capabilities in the company, including loitering munitions (Switchblade), Integrated Air & Missile Defense (Titan RF CUAS jammer, Freedom Eagle – 1 Counter UAS Missile), and Electronic Warfare. He genuinely loves putting amazing capabilities in the hands of our warfighters. Rich volunteers as the Chair of the Staff Parish Relations Team at his church and is the Board Chair for a 501c3 called Still Serving Veterans (SSV.org) that provides veteran career transition services, VA benefit and claims services, and veteran support services, where we connect veterans with urgent needs such as food and financial support with a responsive network of service providers. When he’s not working at AV or supporting SSV, you will find him going to his grandchildren’s basketball games, gymnastics competitions, recitals, etc., and just trying to be the best husband, father, PopPop, and Christian he can be, or working as the CFO and general helper for his wife’s MulberryAcres.us business where she sells locally grown daylilies, irises, natives, fresh blueberries and blackberries, and more. He can be reached at r.mcadams@outlook.com | 256-658-5941."
