    "Edited Writeup": "Pilar McDermott Pilar lives in Yorktown Heights in the Hudson Valley of New York. She has lived in 26 houses over her lifetime, including multiple moves during her Army career. She is divorced with two adult children, including a daughter who rowed competitively. Pilar served 27 years in the Army, initially branching Chemical but transitioning to intelligence, artillery, and strategy positions. She was selected to return to West Point to teach history, earned her PhD in Renaissance Reformation history at the University of Pennsylvania, and spent her final decade as a history professor and division chief of the international division at the Academy. She worked closely with Kevin McKelvey and Karen Phelps during her cadet years. Since retiring, she has worked as a leadership consultant with the Thayer Leadership Group, delivers keynotes, and conducts staff rides with corporate leaders. She also teaches part-time at the Baseball Hall of Fame in Cooperstown, covering topics from civil rights and Jackie Robinson to labor history through baseball. Pilar is an accomplished competitive ballroom dancer, having started five months after beginning lessons and winning multiple competitions including the Empire Dance Sport Championship. She competes in international Latin styles—Cha Cha, Samba, Rumba, Paso Doble, and Jive—at high-level competitions in the New York area and nationally. She trains with European and Blackpool champions and competes regularly at events including the New York Dance Festival in February, Manhattan Dance Sport Championship over July 4th weekend, and the United States Dance Sport Championship in Orlando the week after Labor Day. She can be reached at pilar.mcdermott@yahoo.com | 845-401-9122."
