    "Edited Writeup": "Doug  lives in Novi, Michigan. He has three daughters: Laura, 39, who manages a bar and restaurant; and Allie, 29, and Melanie, 25, who each work at McDowell & Associates. All three live in Michigan. He is in a long-term relationship with Angela, the recently promoted Vice President of Research at Texas A & M, who has two children: Trevor, a Junior at Texas A & M, and Erica, a high school Sophomore at Michigan State University. His cadet experience centered on Glee Club, which he considers the most meaningful part of his West Point experience; traveling nationally, staying in classmate and host homes, forming the small vocal group \"The Group Tones,\" and singing at Medal of Honor events at the Superintendent's quarters, where he shook General Jimmy Doolittle's hand. His Army highlight was serving as an armor officer with 11th Armored Cavalry Regiment on the East-West German border during the Cold War. He served as a scout platoon leader and cavalry troop executive officer in West Germany, lived with German families, and witnessed the fall of East Germany firsthand. He left the Army after completing Armor Officer Advanced Course at the four-year mark and joined Procter & Gamble for two years managing warehouse operations and maintenance teams. He then transitioned into the family firm, McDowell & Associates, a geotechnical and environmental engineering company founded by his uncle. He earned a master's degree in civil/environmental engineering from Wayne State while working full-time and is now president of the firm, leading roughly 65 employees. Current interests outside McDowell & Associates include travelling to Texas and coaching track and field. Doug founded and coaches a youth track club producing nationally ranked athletes, and spent over a decade with the West Point Field Force recruiting candidates from Detroit and underserved communities. Doug can be reached at 313-400-6826 and doug.mcdowell@mcdowasc.com."
