    "Edited Writeup": "Jay Millen Jay lives in Charleston, South Carolina. He and his wife Ginger have two children: daughter Zoe (21), a senior at Rose Hulman majoring in electrical engineering, and son Nate (19), a freshman at Ole Miss in their 5-year accounting master's program. His plebe company was H3, graduating from E2. His most memorable cadet experience was Company E-2's spectacular party on the Supe's boat firstie year. He was responsible for planning and made a slight math error on the alcohol requisition, resulting in even their OIC becoming more celebratory than appropriate. They had a rough landing at South Dock and a nighttime E&E back to the barracks. He served at the NTC, Fort Benning, France, and Latin America. His most fun assignment was as OPFOR at Fort Benning where he got to see and visit with classmates at each rotation. After the Army, he got into business with a Tenneco subsidiary and after helping with the divestiture effort went to International Paper, mainly abroad. He landed with Accenture leading the resources M&A group out of London. When he returned to the US in 2006, he got into executive recruiting and board services, initially with Korn Ferry. He will retire from the executive side in August with Caldwell and transition into board advisory only along with the diaconate in the Anglican Church. He's been truly blessed and giving back is his primary focus at this stage with local charities and initiatives started by the class. He enjoys travel, fishing, and just gathering and catching up. He can be reached at jmillen@caldwellpartners.com | 786-740-9514."
