    "Town": "Melbourne",
    "State": "FL",
    "Edited Writeup": "Darren Moore Darren lives in Melbourne, Florida. He has been married to his wife Yong for 36 years. His oldest stepson is 49 and lives in Norman, Oklahoma with Darren's three granddaughters, ages 24, 22, and 19. His youngest stepson is 48, retired as a West Point DMI instructor, and lives in Fort Montgomery, New York with two granddaughters, ages 23 and 21. His daughter is 30 and lives in Houston, Texas, and his son is 28 and lives in Denver. Darren remembers hosting cadets at his house in Huntington Beach, California for the Army Navy game at the Rose Bowl during yearling year. He attended Fort Rucker for OBC and flight school in 86-87, then served 87-89 in the 55th Aviation Company at K-16 in Songnam, Korea as XO, Ops Officer, and Platoon Leader with eight classmates, flying VIPs into the JSA, DMZ, and supporting the 88 Summer Olympics. He returned to Fort Rucker for Advanced Course in 89-90, then served as Brigade Ops Officer with the 8th Infantry Division in Mainz, Germany in 90-91, deploying to Iraq for Operation Provide Comfort. From 91-92 he was a pharmaceutical rep for Allergan and a USAR Captain in the 168th Aviation Group in Los Alamitos, California. He served 92-00 as an active duty helicopter pilot for the US Coast Guard in Miami and Puerto Rico. From 00-22 he flew rotary wing, Predator B, and fixed wing aircraft for US Customs in Miami, Oklahoma City, Cocoa Beach, and Jacksonville, with drug interdiction missions in Miami being his most interesting role. He retired as a Coast Guard O6 in 2022 after assignments with Coast Guard Group Miami, USTRANSCOM, Coast Guard Institute, and USNORTHCOM. He and Yong moved to Melbourne, Florida after retirement and travel extensively. Darren enjoys drinking beer and laughing about cadet and life adventures with classmates. He can be reached at darrenmmoore@sbcglobal.net | 405-778-0125."
