    "Edited Writeup": "Mick Murray resides in Tustin, California, where he serves as a Superior Court Judge hearing criminal cases. Contact information includes (714) 454-5688 and mfmurray145@gmail.com. He described his cadet experience through shared stories, recalling as a highlight a Cow-year episode involving post-Easter treats that escalated into a memorable prank. His most significant Army assignment was serving as a scout platoon leader, which he cited as the most enjoyable period of his service due to the role’s pace and responsibility. He resigned his commission in 1991, attended law school in California, spent 25 years as a prosecuting attorney, including a decade focused on cold-case homicides, retired from prosecution in 2016, and became a Superior Court Judge in 2017, a role he continues today. His current interests include skiing, travel, attending sporting events, and gatherings that allow time to reconnect with others, and his family includes three adult children pursuing public service and science careers in Alaska and Hawaii."
