    "Edited Writeup": "Dean Nakadate resides in Bend, Oregon, where he works part-time as a podiatrist and plans to fully retire in the near future. His cadet highlights include playing water polo, dating the post chaplain's daughter, and serving as company commander second semester — an experience he describes as herding firsties with senioritis through SAMI and parades. His Army service took him through Airborne School, Infantry Officer Basic Course, and Ranger School before a posting to Fort Wainwright in Fairbanks, Alaska, where he served as a rifle platoon leader and arctic scout platoon leader. After Alaska he transitioned out of the Army, returned to California for additional schooling, and became a podiatrist — a career choice he credits to someone telling him it was the highest paid job with the most time to go fishing. He spent a decade teaching residents and fellows at Scripps Clinic in La Jolla before relocating to Bend to raise his two sons. Joshua, 25, is a mechanical engineer near Portland who thru-hiked the Pacific Crest Trail at 17, and Nathan, 23, is completing California Maritime Academy and earning his third mate license this summer. Current interests include fishing, skiing, kayaking, travel, coaching water polo, shooting, and good bourbon. Dean can be reached at 541-280-2895 and take1of3@bendbroadband.com."
