    "Edited Writeup": "Andy Napoli Andy lives in Savannah, Georgia, with his wife Robin. Their daughter Katie lives nearby with her husband Toby and two children. Their son Cooper lives in Colorado working in high-performance fitness training. As XO of Bravo Company, 3rd Engineer Battalion during Desert Storm, he oversaw deployment of heavy equipment through the Port of Savannah. When logistical delays prompted General Barry McCaffrey to fire the Navy and longshoremen, Andy and fellow exos loaded the ships themselves despite having no training. He later helped offload equipment in Saudi Arabia. He served as a company commander in Hawaii, attended grad school, taught at West Point, and transitioned to civilian life after 16 years. He joined Progressive Insurance with help from an '87 grad and moved several times for career opportunities before settling in Savannah. He and Robin now run a business downtown above their shop. He grew up in Cornwall, New York, 15 minutes from West Point, where his father worked in the admissions office. His best friend growing up was classmate Dean Dorman, and they joined West Point together. He travels and welcomes classmates to visit Savannah. He can be reached at Andy_Napoli@yahoo.com | 312-965-2032."
