    "Edited Writeup": "Jim Nickolas Jim lives in Mansfield, Texas near family. His plebe company was F4.He recalls his father calling out to him during the Acceptance Day parade, a moment that mixed discipline with family pride. He also remembers a steady stream of bootleg boxes from home and the improbable streak of his parents winning the Thayer Hotel lottery for every major event. His identity as a cadet was shaped by soccer, a workmanlike approach to the regimen, and quiet determination to stay squared away. He served four years at the National Training Center. His career path included Korea, SAMS, battalion command in Baghdad during the surge (deployed understrength with inadequate facilities and broken equipment, leading a dispersed, high-tempo fight), War College, and DAIG investigations including Abu Ghraib. His battalion command in Baghdad stands out as his defining experience, citing the adaptability and resilience of soldiers under those conditions. His later work inspecting global detention operations under the DAIG also carried strategic weight. He earned multiple graduate degrees through Army schooling, then used the GI Bill to attend law school after retiring. He practiced estate planning briefly in Kansas before moving to Texas, taking the state bar, and running a small firm. His current vocation centers on church service and board work for a coffee company. He is active in his church and community. He can be reached at jamesdnickolas@icloud.com."
