    "Edited Writeup": "Clay Olbon Clay lives in Lilburn, Georgia. He is married to Becky, whom he met at Fort Campbell some 35+ years ago. They have two kids - one in the workforce and one just finishing undergrad, with no grandchildren yet. His plebe company was F1. His most memorable cadet experiences were watching Father Matt break dance in the hallway as a firstie, trying to get a paper airplane from the 6th floor window of the barracks to diagonal walk (great being in E-3), and his 3-man firstie room all selecting infantry and Fort Campbell as their assignment. His only post was Fort Campbell, Kentucky, where he loved being a TOW company XO as his last job. After the Army, he worked for a small defense contractor in Huntsville, Alabama, moved to Detroit to work for a hospital as a systems administrator, worked for a dot-com startup and moved to Atlanta. He's spent the past 20+ years working for big consulting companies as an IT consultant, almost 19 years at Accenture where he's planning to retire. He currently leads their Accenture Song (their digital agency) portfolio for a large media and entertainment client. He spends most of his free time helping out at his church (leading adult Bible study among other things) and cycling with a local club. He enjoys cycling, baseball games, and Army football. He can be reached at olbonc@yahoo.com | 678-471-6010."
