    "Edited Writeup": "Greg Ortiz Greg lives in El Paso, Texas. He has no grandchildren. His 27-year-old daughter lives in New York City working as a journalist, and his 25-year-old son lives in Los Angeles as an audio producer for Disney. His plebe company was H4, graduating from D3. He was a frustrated musician at West Point who tried to get a band going with classmates Bob Penna and Jim Seramba, though it never materialized. His most rewarding memory was working on the 100th-night show when he and classmate Mike Gwynn sat down at his electric keyboard - Gwynn gave him direction and lyrics, and he composed the music, calling it an amazing collaboration. He served 5 years as an MI officer with no command or combat tours. He attended Airborne school as an officer after OBC, completed OBC and OAC at Fort Huachuca, and served a 3-year tour in Stuttgart, Germany in various staff and support positions, the most interesting of which was Battalion Maintenance Officer. He served as Squadron S-2 for the 5th ID Cavalry but resigned his commission before their rotation to the NTC. After the Army, he was a public high school math and engineering teacher in El Paso ISD for 26 years, the only time he got close to using his Management Engineering degree. He is one of the \"Puerto Rico Four\" - all four attended the same high school in San Juan at the DoD school on Fort Buchanan. The three other graduates include Steve Sicinski (who was also in D-3 with him), John Badovinac, and non-graduate Kevin Burns. He enjoys seeing classmates in casual settings without structured activities required. He can be reached at lgortiz222@gmail.com | 915-731-5975."
