    "Edited Writeup": "Rich lives in Raleigh, NC with his wife Lou. They have two children and one grandchild. Their son lives in Oregon and their daughter in North Carolina. Rich and Lou have been married for 38 years after dating in high school and on and off through West Point. After graduation she dumped him, but a few years later he was able to woo her back. He served in field artillery, mostly at Fort Stewart, Georgia with the 24th ID. The highlight was being deployed to Operations Desert Shield and Desert Storm. Following active duty, he joined the North Carolina National Guard in 1991 and stayed through 1999, achieving the rank of major. In 2016 he was selected as a Civilian Aide to the Secretary of the Army for the state of California. He started his career as a sales rep in the pharmaceutical business and has remained in that industry for 35 years, leading five companies as CEO and continuing to serve on various boards of directors. He recently joined a venture capital fund as a senior advisor. He's active as a board member on the Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund, which gives scholarships to children of the fallen in honor of classmate John McHugh. He enjoys travel, professional sports, mini reunions at Army football games, and boating. He can be reached at rwpascoe86@gmail.com | 858-342-4741."
