    "Edited Writeup": "Gary Pearcy Gary lives in Rehoboth Beach, Delaware with his wife Laurie. Both of their children, Emily and Kyle, live in New Orleans. They visit frequently as they are smitten with their two-year-old granddaughter, Poppy Mae. Gary has too many memories to enumerate but when you had roommates like Ken Carrick (RIP), Rob Healy, Tim Knight, John Lazar, and Paul Kapsner, one can only imagine. His B-3 Bandit company mates are an incredible group. He spent 12 years as an Army aviator, serving as UH-60 platoon leader, company commander (82nd Airborne), and in other roles. He served in Operation Desert Storm, deploying from Nurnberg, Germany with 4th Squadron, 2nd Armored Cavalry Regiment, and spent a lot of time at Fort Rucker, Alabama. After leaving the military, he joined corporate America, first at GE, then honed his payments skills working at Wells Fargo and then in the fintech world. He celebrated his retirement in January 2025 and has not looked back. He and Laurie took a nice long trip to Italy in May and are planning their next vacation abroad, hopefully next spring. Gary loves traveling, playing golf, and enjoying a beautiful sunset. He can be reached at pearcyge@yahoo.com | 612-599-4101."
