    "Edited Writeup": "Barry Peterson Barry lives in Reno, Nevada. He is married with no children. His plebe company was C4. He remembers C-4's strong plebe cohort and later E-3's Sandhurst culture, where excellence, physicality, and unit pride aligned perfectly with his identity. His defining experience was serving as an infantry platoon leader after earning his Ranger tab and joining the 82nd Airborne. Just Cause influenced his decision to leave as he reevaluated priorities after the deployment. He transitioned first to Goodyear tire plant as a quality assurance engineer while earning an MBA. A knee injury and curiosity about human-machine performance led him into graduate work in virtual reality at the University of Washington and later to the Naval Postgraduate School, where he built simulation and training systems. After 9/11 he left DOD and spent over a decade as a full-time Bikram yoga teacher and trainer. He continues advocating for soldier resilience. He credits classmates for key course corrections. He can be reached at barrynpeterson@gmail.com | 775-636-4334."
