    "Town": "Ashburn",
    "State": "VA",
    "Edited Writeup": "MaryEllen (Conway) Picciuto ME lives in Ashburn, Virginia. She has been married nearly 40 years to her cadet sweetheart Jack Picciuto, USMA '84. Her daughter, 36, recently moved to Australia with her boyfriend after serving 11+ years as an Air Force intelligence officer. Her son, 33, lives in Huntington Beach, California where he works for an intelligence systems manufacturing and development company. He is married since 2018 and is a former Army intelligence officer who served 10 years. No grandchildren yet. ME's favorite cadet memories are Graduation, Ring Weekend, and when they were finally allowed in the Firstie Club. She served as a Quartermaster officer assigned to 13th COSCOM at Fort Hood, followed by 3rd Armored Division in Hanau, Germany. She deployed to Desert Shield and Storm and departed the Army in August 1991 to be a better (nondeployed) mother to her daughter, who was just eight months old when MaryEllen left for the desert. After hanging up her BDUs, she was a military spouse for another 20 years through lots of PCSs. She was a stay-at-home mom for 10 years, worked as a government civilian including 2.5 years as the \"Cadet Hostess\" at West Point, and held nonprofit manager and executive positions with lots of gratifying volunteer work. Her most interesting, challenging, and rewarding role was starting up (with Steve Cannon and Tony Guzzi) and leading the nonprofit Johnny Mac Soldiers Fund from inception to $50 million raised for scholarships for military children of the fallen or disabled. She retired in 2025 after 11 years in that career-culminating job and is finding she loves not working. She co-founded the Chicks of '86 with Julie DelGiorno and Carolyn Elliot-Lewis in 2010 to strengthen the bonds of women '86 classmates through annual gatherings and enhanced communications. She grew up just off Highway 9 in Freehold, New Jersey, home of \"The Boss,\" and is a Jersey girl through and through—she loves Springsteen, pizza, and not pumping her own gas.MaryEllen always enjoys catching up with classmates at reunions, on travel, Army sports events, or her favorite, a good happy hour. She can be reached at me.picciuto@gmail.com | 845-926-7875."
