    "State": "NC",
    "Edited Writeup": "Scott Pierce Scott lives in Cary, North Carolina. He has been married for 27 years and has three daughters: his oldest is an LTJG JAG in the US Navy after graduating from law school; his middle daughter is a UNC graduate and now a professional soccer player for Shelbourne in the Premier League of Ireland; and his youngest is striving to become an industrial engineer. His plebe company was G1 and he graduated from H4. His most memorable cadet experiences include the company boxing rivalries with G4 and I4, and seeing Bruce Springsteen in the Meadowlands in 1985 with classmates. He served in the 2nd ACR on the East-West German border when the walls came down, then left active duty to become a bond trader for JP Morgan and traded through the Asian debt crisis and fall of Long Term Capital Markets, then left the business to reenter the military in various special operations roles after the attacks of Sept 11th. He re-entered bond trading after the military break to help start a trading firm that eventually was sold to Banco Santander, so he continues to travel to NYC to complete the integration of the 2 firms. He enjoys working as a Field Force member in North Carolina interacting with West Point candidates, noting that these kids are a lot sharper than most of us were. He enjoys pickleball, canicross (running races with his dog) and leading the Second Dragoons Firepit Foundation (a 501c3). He can be reached at spierce86@gmail.com | 203-979-7083."
