    "Town": "Medart",
    "State": "FL",
    "Edited Writeup": "Ed Pigott Ed Pigott lives in Medart, Florida, recently returned to his hometown after decades away. His older daughter, 31, lives in Brooklyn with her fiancé and works as a speech pathologist on travel assignments after studying in Colorado and Georgia. His younger daughter studied engineering and accounting at Colorado State University and now works in banking in Hampton, Virginia. Both daughters are independent and off the payroll. He served as an armor officer, drawn to the branch by lifelong familiarity with heavy equipment, and trained on older armored vehicles before the M1 at Fort Polk, where he valued the tight-knit group of classmates stationed there. He left the Army in 1990 during the post-Cold War drawdown and transitioned into manufacturing through a West Point connection. His civilian career spanned senior roles in heavy manufacturing, precision machining, energy, aerospace supply chains, and industrial operations across multiple states, frequently leading turnarounds and plant closures. He later became plant manager of solar PV module manufacturing after working for Exxon making gas pumps. He adopted RV living while continuing contract and leadership roles before entering semi-retirement. His cadet memories focus on B2 as a plebe and later G4, including being assigned to remedial marching due to lack of rhythm, then later becoming training sergeant and winning the guide-on for G4. He travels extensively by RV, visiting classmates across the country and combining travel with informal social connection through shared meals, reunions, and sporting events. He lives part-time in an RV on family land about 100 yards from the house he grew up in and is considering coaching youth sports. He can be reached at edgarpigott@gmail.com | 719-553-7798."
