    "Edited Writeup": "Bret Platt Bret and his wife Janet live in Rome, Pennsylvania, approaching their 40th anniversary in June 2026. They have four grown children, three sons and a daughter. They also have two grandchildren. Bret's first assignment took him to a Special Weapons unit in Longare, Italy, near Vicenza, where he worked multiple company grade positions before the site was decommissioned. After the advanced course he spent the bulk of his Army career at Fort Stewart and Hunter Army Airfield, moving through the Division Ammo Office, 724th Main Support Battalion, 24th Ordnance Company as commander, 260th Quartermaster Battalion, and the 24th Corps Support Group. His final military assignment was Maintenance Officer at Letterkenny Army Depot in Chambersburg, Pennsylvania. Leaving the Army in 1995, he worked program and project management consulting across Army depots, Air Force Air Logistics Centers, and after relocating to the DC area, multiple federal clients including TSA, DHS, EPA, Coast Guard, FEMA, DOL, DISA, and DLA. In 2016 he returned to federal service with the DLA Defense Agencies Initiative program office, retiring December 31, 2024 as DAI Portfolio Manager. He can be reached at bplatt62@gmail.com | 540-841-4172."
