    "Edited Writeup": "David Pratt resides in Salinas, California, where he is fully retired and focused on family life and personal projects. He can be reached at dpratt245@comcast.net. As a cadet, he described his most meaningful experiences as occurring off campus rather than in formal settings of West Point. His cadet highlights consisted of traveling to away games, spending weekends with classmates’ families, visiting nearby relatives, and getting outside the wire during demanding academic terms, which he recalled as essential for recharging and maintaining balance. His most significant Army assignment followed graduation from OBC and flight school at Fort Rucker, when he served in the Aviation Brigade at Fort Ord in support of the 7th Infantry Division, including a deployment to Panama in 1989 as part of a joint task force immediately preceding Operation Just Cause; he resigned his commission in 1991 and ETS’d in the Monterey Bay area. After military service, he worked first in private manufacturing and later in the public sector in construction management and capital projects management for local government agencies, culminating in full retirement in 2024. Current interests include gardening, local hiking, RV travel, fly fishing in the Sierra Nevada, Army football travel, camping, home improvement projects, and spending time with his children and first grandchild."
