    "Edited Writeup": "LaVon Purnell-Wilson LaVon lives in Norfolk, Virginia. She has a 39-year-old stepson in Springfield, Ohio, a 37-year-old stepdaughter who is a police officer in Las Vegas, and a 34-year-old goddaughter near Atlanta. She has four grandchildren: granddaughters aged 16 and 6, and grandsons aged 8 and 5. LaVon served 28+ years in the Signal Corps. She commanded the 58th Signal Battalion in Okinawa, Japan and later served as commander of NATO Sector Norfolk under the NATO Communications and Information Systems Agency. As a cadet, she ran indoor and outdoor track and sang in the Cadet Gospel Choir. Since retiring, she served as Board Chair for the Crispus Attucks Cultural Center in Norfolk and founded Ocean Dreams Vacation Rentals, also in Norfolk. LaVon enjoys traveling and would welcome opportunities to travel with classmates. She can be reached at lavon.purnell@gmail.com | 703-434-9342."
