    "Edited Writeup": "Bill Pursel Weas lives in Watkins, Colorado. His daughter Kristin has a two-year-old son, CJ, living in Cincinnati. He served in short-range air defense and later as a Patriot officer. During Desert Storm he and a three-soldier crew shot down five Scuds, earning a Bronze Star. He valued his Germany tour, teaching the Patriot course at Fort Bliss, and the sustained camaraderie with soldiers he still hears from decades later. He entered sales with General Mills, then spent more than twenty years with Lawson Products in sales and sales leadership, including running military/government sales. After moving to Denver he worked for UPS, the Postal Service, United Airlines catering operations, and then 7-Eleven, where he has served in food safety, quality assurance, and financial planning and analysis for eight years. He survived brain cancer after surgery, chemo, and radiation, aided by classmate Jeff Thramann's guidance. He maintains a 10,000-steps-a-day streak approaching 3,300 consecutive days—almost nine years. He is deeply involved in veterans' organizations, served five years as VFW quartermaster, and continues hands-on support to veterans and surviving families. He and his wife Jenn completed visits to all 50 states and now live in Colorado with their two Shih Tzus, Fireball and Merlin. He attends chess tournaments and sporting events, and values time with friends. He can be reached at billpursel@aol.com | 513-477-5708."
