    "Edited Writeup": "Jaimy (Just) Rand Jaimy lives in Harborcreek, PA with her husband Frank. They've been married for 35 years and have one daughter in her final year of undergrad. She was a plebe in A-2 and an upperclassman in H-3, where the company became the H-3 Hamsters and acquired a mascot hamster named Sparky who lived in her room with roommate Leanne Garner. She commissioned into the MP Corps and after company command transitioned to Acquisition Corps. After grad school at University of Texas, she served in testing, contracting, and program management roles with her final assignment as Commander, Fort Hood Contracting Command. Stateside she was assigned to Fort McClellan, Fort Hood, and the Pentagon, and overseas to Pirmasens and Heidelberg, Germany. She deployed to the Balkans and to Iraq. One of her most memorable assignments was two years in DC, where the first year she led the ASAALT team in the Army ten miler and exactly one year later she and Frank had their daughter Reagan. After Army retirement she was employed at General Electric in Erie, PA establishing agreements for freight locomotive engineered systems, then went back to federal service at the VA in various contracting roles. She and Frank are both retired and like to stay active, take advantage of the flexibility for travel, and play golf. She can be reached at jaimyrand@yahoo.com | 254-220-3032."
