    "Edited Writeup": "Mike Reed Mike lives in Geneva, Illinois. He and his wife Maureen have two adult children. Their son Travis is an electrical and computer engineer who also programs high-tolerance machining systems and once interned on analytics code still used today. Their daughter Olivia is married and lives across town in the Chicago area. His plebe company was C4. He remembers escaping to the library stacks during plebe stress, exploring old Howitzers, and listening to music where no one would haze him. His defining professional moment was receiving both a Bradley platoon and then an entire mortar platoon that he rehabilitated before Reforger 88, accumulating nearly three years of platoon-leader time. After the Army, he moved directly into engineering with Parsons, running and commissioning power plants at a prison, then UCLA, and later globally, leading to major field roles in Iraq and Nigeria. During the 2000s he shifted into industrial predictive analytics, joining SmartSignal, then GE, and later InStep and Schneider/AVEVA. He now works in an AI center of excellence integrating analytics across industrial software systems. He has lived and worked on four continents, survived malaria, dealt with corruption in Nigeria, and black-started UCLA's power plant after the Northridge earthquake. He met his wife while both were serving in West Germany. His lifelong interests center on reading history, hiking, outdoor activity, and soccer, which he has played continuously since childhood. He still enjoys physical challenges and high-adventure outdoor settings. He can be reached at reedmt5@msn.com | 630-232-7801."
