    "Edited Writeup": "Dan Rizzo Riz lives in Nokesville, Virginia. He has two sons: Michael, 28, who lives in the Chicago area and works in game design with a strong interest in Bitcoin and technology, and David, 25, who graduated from Purdue with a degree in mechanical engineering and works in a civil engineering lab focusing on concrete testing. Both sons live near their mother in the Chicago area. Dan is divorced. He served with 5th Infantry Division, stationed at Fort Polk as both platoon leader and XO, and later worked in public affairs. A standout moment was getting a tank airborne at NTC by driving full speed over a hill. He also trained at Jungle School with classmates like Chris \"Bumper\" Greer. After leaving the Army, he worked primarily in small manufacturing companies, especially fasteners. While living in the Chicago area, he designed and built a mobile wood-fired pizza oven and launched a business selling pizza at farmers markets and catering private events. He pursued an MBA at Northwestern in the late 1990s. He was one of the oldest cadets in the class, turning 22 at R-Day, and came to West Point after time in the Army and at the University of Minnesota. He's active in the Unity Call, a confidential peer-support group for classmates. He skis, scuba dives, and cooks. He can be reached at dannyrizzo@hotmail.com | 847-721-9236."
