    "Edited Writeup": "Dean lives in Hershey, Pennsylvania, with his wife Sharon (Loveless), USMA '88; they have three daughters named Echo, Chosin, and Thayer. As a cadet, he served as a Rabble Rouser, and his signature moment came at Veterans Stadium during the Army-Navy walk-on, where he directed the crowd from high in the stands — concealing beneath his Rabble Rouser uniform a bright red jersey bearing #30, a silent protest against Navy's redshirting of star running back Napoleon McCallum. A prior slug kept him from ever revealing it. His most significant Army assignments centered on aerial reconnaissance: flying the border of North Korea in an RU-21H, operating \"somewhere in Central America\" in an RC-12H, and becoming the first Army Aviator qualified in the RC-12N, after which he trained the next generation of Army reconnaissance pilots at Fort Huachuca, AZ. After military service, he flew for FedEx and USAir before spending more than 20 years teaching Statistics at Hershey High School. Current interests include golf at unpretentious public courses and attending sporting events. Warren can be reached at 717-533-2358 and intel17@aol.com."
