    "Edited Writeup": "Dan Sauter Dan lives in Huntsville, Alabama. He has four children: Daniel and Leora (with Danny and Emma) in Philadelphia; Michael and Julia (with Leni and Roman) at Cannon AFB, New Mexico; Matthew and Olivia at Fort Leonard Wood heading to Fort Hood; and Jack at Cornell in New York City. Dan's best leadership experience was watching Coach Jim Young lead Army football back to a winning tradition. His favorite story or memory: pick any day in G-3, the company in the best class. He had the opportunity to serve with and help develop young American men and women over 27 years. After the Army, he worked for Lockheed Martin, where he has retired, and is currently with a startup. The Sauters were stationed with Rob (Rogge) Roggeman and family at six different duty locations. Mick Haydak and Rogge are godfathers to two of their boys. Dan enjoys sports, Army events, golf, and travel. He can be reached at dansauter3@gmail.com | 760-267-7079."
