    "Edited Writeup": "Eric Schacht Eric lives in Kansas City, Missouri and remains single after divorcing in 2014 following 24 years of marriage. He has two children: Meg Ross is married to an Army Field Artillery Major stationed at Fort Stewart, Georgia. Meg and Geoff have two daughters, Emma (13) and Elli (9), and Geoff is currently deployed to Poland. Brian is an aviator married to Caisley Schacht (Ladd), daughter of Keith and Claudia Ladd (Class of '87). They have two daughters, Maeve (5) and Josie (2), and are currently stationed at Fort Huachuca, Arizona, where Brian works as a fixed wing aviator for T2COM. He lost his middle child Justin in 2007 when he was 15 and a half. His plebe company was G2, graduating from D3. His most memorable cadet experience was the 150-pound football game at Cornell as a freshman when he and Jim Howard got hauled out of a frat house after the game by their Senior OR, Colonel Jim Kays, well after midnight. He commanded 1-26 Infantry with a couple of trips to Iraq in 2004-2005 and 2006-2007, describing them as tough times in that theater. Since retiring from active duty in 2016, he has been a facilitator at the School of Command Preparation, preparing battalion commanders and command sergeants major for their roles. He enjoys golf outings, Army games, freshwater fishing outings, and travel. He can be reached at ericschacht@icloud.com | 706-993-5431."
