    "Edited Writeup": "Dan Schafer Dan lives in Naples, Florida, with his wife Kimberly. He has four biological children and one stepdaughter. His oldest daughter lives in Chicago, is married, and works in theater and fitness management. His son is a former high-level collegiate wrestler who now coaches wrestling at the University of Arkansas at Little Rock. His second daughter lives in New York City and works professionally in musical theater. His youngest biological daughter lives in South Carolina and works as a chef. His stepdaughter is a college student in Alabama studying commercial interior design. No grandchildren yet, though several \"granddogs.\" He served as a field artillery officer in light units, including airborne-capable artillery, with assignments in California and Fort Sill. He attended Ranger School to build credibility supporting infantry units and later taught officer basic courses. He left active duty in the early 1990s after the birth of his first child and transitioned into civilian sales. He initially sold medical products, then moved into technology sales where he built a long career. His current role focuses on business development and new client acquisition, a position he has held for approximately 15 years. He grew up in Normal, Illinois, wrestled competitively, and was recruited to West Point primarily for wrestling. He travels for work and makes a point of reconnecting with classmates wherever business takes him. He can be reached at rangerdan86@gmail.com | 405-245-8044."
