    "Town": "Acworth",
    "State": "GA",
    "Edited Writeup": "Al lives in Acworth, Georgia. He has a daughter Allison, a son Stephen, a grandson Caden (currently 6 years old), and a granddaughter on the way in May 2026. His plebe company was A1, graduating from H4. His favorite memories are of his time in the Cadet Glee Club. Besides his love for music, they had a chance to travel throughout the United States, meet great people and a few celebrities, and be ambassadors for West Point. They sang at a Bob Hope tribute in Hollywood, California and met a number of actors of his day including Charlton Heston, Jimmy Stewart, Robert Stack, and Chuck Connors. Most of his time was served in an attack helicopter battalion in Germany. He was assigned to the second Army unit to be fielded with the Apache helicopter. His most interesting assignments were deploying to Israel to train the Israeli Air Force to fly and fight the AH-64 Apache, and deployment for Operations Desert Shield and Desert Storm conducting the Army's first-ever, cross-FLOT, night deep attack with the AH-64. After the Army, he attended Duke University for his MBA, worked as a Manager at Coopers & Lybrand (now PriceWaterhouseCoopers), served as M&A executive at multiple companies, and as SVP at Alfa Insurance. He currently owns a manufacturing company (commercial cabinetry) in Calhoun, Georgia, specializing in cabinetry for the child care industry and shipping nationwide. He played in bands for 30 years and has a recording studio in his home. He enjoys golf, fishing, and attending Army football games (home or road). He can be reached at alschellhorn@yahoo.com | 205-908-7565."
