    "Edited Writeup": "Thatch Shepard resides in Ridgeland, Mississippi, where he is retired following a long career in engineering and public service. Contact information includes (601) 278-2615 and thatchjennie@aol.com. He did not offer a general self-characterization of his cadet experience, but his cadet highlight was participating in the March On at the 1985 Army–Navy game after dressing his younger brothers as cadets, an episode shared with a classmate. His Army career spanned 27 years of active duty, culminating in retirement from the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers in Vicksburg, with assignments including Fort Belvoir, Fort Riley, Fort Benning, Schofield Barracks, New Orleans, the University of Florida, West Point as a professor of environmental engineering, Belgium with SHAPE/NATO, Savannah, and Vicksburg, and included managing levee demolition during the 2011 flood. After military service, he worked in private engineering before returning to the Corps of Engineers as a civilian, including a period serving while a classmate was Chief of Engineers. His current interests include Ole Miss football, boating, and spending time at the beach, and his family includes three children and five grandchildren. Two of his children are also West Point graduates."
