    "Edited Writeup": "Tim's plebe company was B1, and he graduated from D2. His most memorable cadet experience was graduating, and realizing that he would never have to go back to our Rockbound Highland Home, except of his own accord. He served with 3/325th Airborne Combat Team in Vicenza, Italy. After the Army, Tim earned a Ph. D. in mathematics from the University of California - Santa Barbara, and went on to become a Professor of Mathematics at Weber State University. Tim and his wife Emily now split their time between their house in Italy and Ogden, Utah. They spend most of every summer climbing, backpacking, and hiking in the Sierra of California. He can be reached at thsteele@weber.edu | 801-247-2189."
