    "Edited Writeup": "Mike Stradinger resides in Mission Hills, Kansas, where he is active as a lawyer, manufacturer, company founder, and investor with a focus on manufacturing. Contact information includes (816) 304-4553 and mstradinger@holland1916.com. Graduation is his favorite cadet memory. His most significant Army service was as an engineer officer at Fort Belvoir and at U.S. Army Corps of Engineers Headquarters, where he worked in the Office of Strategic Planning for the Chief of Engineers, an assignment notable for its exposure to enterprise-level planning and institutional decision-making. After military service, he pursued a civilian career spanning law, manufacturing leadership, company formation, and investment, building a portfolio of roles centered on creating and scaling industrial enterprises. His current interests include travel, reading, skiing, fishing, and golf, and he is involved in the emerging field of cognitive warfare and narrative intelligence. His family includes three married children and three grandchildren, with a fourth grandchild expected."
