    "State": "AL",
    "Edited Writeup": "Michael Switzer Mike lives in Madison, Alabama with a 26-year-old daughter. He stays connected with the H-3 hurricane community—about 18 classmates gather regularly in the Huntsville area. His military career centered on Army aviation, culminating as Program Manager at Redstone Arsenal where he oversaw five helicopter fleets including the OH-58D Kiowa Warrior. At one point 40% of the Kiowa fleet was deployed under his watch. A family highlight came during a military exchange assignment with the RAF in the UK, certifying British Apaches for combat deployment. Before that, memorable Academy experiences included scuba diving, a Panama Canal transit, summer flight training, and a project at Lawrence Livermore Labs. He also helped lead the H3 group—alongside Mike McMahon '85 and others—that ran onto the field in bathrobes during the ESPN Air Force game to spell out \"Beat AFA.\" After the Army he works as a civilian in acquisition programs supporting aviation, space, and missile systems. He manages Foreign Military Sales cases, particularly with British partners, finding that work rewarding. His family appeared in LIFE magazine in December 1999 with an update in 2000. He can be reached at switz86@aol.com | 772-214-9984."
