    "Edited Writeup": "Roy Tomlinson Roy lives in Tokyo, Japan and has no children. His plebe company was D1, graduating from E2. He has many memorable cadet stories, including having tea with Dusty Scott in the Supe's residence yearling year. He had led a spirit mission to steal the sign off the Supe's lawn, and after fingers pointed at him, he was given an order to return the sign and apologize. Mrs. Scott, always a kind person, invited him in for tea and they had a delightful 30 minutes getting to know each other over tea and cookies. He reported to his TAC that he had indeed apologized and Mrs. Scott had accepted the apology. His most memorable assignment was being in Germany when the wall went down, which he describes as surreal. After the Army, he's been an international school teacher for over 25 years in Singapore, Manila, Tokyo, and Kathmandu. He served as President of the West Point Society of Singapore for 6 years, got the Singaporean grads involved, and they now run the society. He would enjoy hosting mini-reunions in Japan. He can be reached at roytomlinson86@gmail.com | +81 70 9077 2910."
