    "Edited Writeup": "Trey Tumminello Trey lives in Raphine, Virginia with his wife Dana, whom he married shortly after graduation. They have two children and five grandchildren. AJ (USMA 2013) is an intelligence officer stationed at the US Embassy in New Delhi, India. Grace, a former UH60 pilot, is married to a USAFA grad, and they are stationed in Aviano, Italy. Trey fondly remembers the \"Grey Berets\" missions into the steam tunnels and late night poker games in the basement trunk room that didn't end well. He served in the infantry in various assignments with the 1st Cavalry Division including Desert Storm, 7th Infantry Division, and 3rd Ranger Battalion. His time with the Ranger Regiment was his favorite, where the quality and dedication of the men, NCOs, and officers was exemplary.  After the Army, Trey and Dana returned to Yorktown, Virginia where he sold medical devices and they raised their two kids. When AJ and Grace left for college and the Army, Trey left his sales job, and he and Dana bought a bed and breakfast in the Shenandoah Valley that they successfully ran for six years. They fell in love with the beauty and slow pace of life in the Valley, and with their kids living overseas, they sold the business in 2025 and remained in the area. They found a \"fixer upper\" with beautiful views of the valley and mountains that Trey is remodeling. Trey enjoys outdoor activities, especially hunting. He and Dana love traveling overseas and are always ready to visit a new exotic country. He can be reached at treytumminello86@gmail.com | 757-254-7099."
