    "Edited Writeup": "Kris Urbauer Kris lives in Oak Lawn, Illinois. Her most meaningful service includes company command at Fort Bragg in an airborne topographic engineer unit, earning Jumpmaster wings on the first attempt, and deploying to Bosnia in 1994 as the lone U.S. topographic engineer with a British team managing safe-route mapping during active shelling. Earlier roles included platoon leadership at Fort Riley, NTC rotations, humanitarian missions in Honduras, and facilities engineering across Korea. She earned a master's degree in geotechnical engineering, became a licensed PE, and joined GE as a Six Sigma Black Belt, later becoming a Master Black Belt and instructor. She moved into regional service leadership, then corporate personnel relations conducting global positive-employee-relations work. Her final and favorite role was running GE's veteran programs and leading the company's veteran network after more than a decade in that senior role. She volunteered for post-9/11 service, was recalled to active duty, and spent a year with the New York District of the Army Corps of Engineers supporting Ground Zero cleanup while living in Manhattan. She now substitute-teaches, including at the grade school she attended. She can be reached at urbs86@comcast.net | 708-704-2391."
