    "Edited Writeup": "John Vickers John lives in Delhi, New York with his wife Beth. They have two sons: Teddy is a chemical engineer in Houston who recently became engaged to his sweetheart Daniella, and Paul is an IT engineer for a hedge fund company in Manhattan. John remembers the D2 tactical officer, CPT Gary Andersen, who had some funny mannerisms, and one of their ex-classmates, Michael Bowers, did a great imitation. Also one time as a practical joke, one of them slathered sticky orange juice on the door handle to one of the rooms and CPT Andersen came by for SAMI and grabbed the handle. John enjoyed aspects of every assignment: Fort Ord as a lieutenant with multiple NTC rotations and lots of golf; Germany as a captain with construction projects all around Germany and travel all over Europe with Beth; ACS at University of Colorado where he learned about water resources and did lots of fishing; US Army Corps of Engineers assignments in Buffalo and Philadelphia where he served as the USACE forward operations officer and then commander for USACE response to 9/11 at the WTC site; ACRC at Fort Drum where he started hunting; and finally running an ROTC Battalion at Northern Michigan University where he commissioned numerous quality officers and did lots of hunting and fishing. Following retirement in 2006, they moved to upstate New York and John started a second career as an engineer in the NYC Water Supply. He ended up as Director of Source Water Operations responsible for leading several hundred people in the delivery of 1.1 billion gallons of high quality drinking water a day to almost half the population of New York State. They retired in 2024 and now are traveling more and enjoying their time together. They hope to start getting around more in the US and seeing classmates. Upstate New York is wonderful in the summer and they have plenty of room, a heated pool, and welcome visitors. John would enjoy travel, golf, fishing, and hunting with classmates. He can be reached at johnbethvickers@gmail.com | 607-437-9117."
