    "Edited Writeup": "Nate Wallace Nate lives in Pilot Valley, Nevada with his wife Anathea Beecher - they've been married 39 years. They are retired on 80 acres of sage brush in the middle of nowhere. He has two kids: a daughter in Alaska and a son at Hill AFB, Utah working as an Air Force civilian. Nate remembers that Army-Navy games were always great times, even the time they had to pay for a shattered toilet before they would let them check out of the hotel from the weekend (Weilep/Saso/Stanko?) during cow year. His highlight was going back to Ranger School as a battalion XO/S3 and watching the students suffer and excel as much as they did in the late 80s - except on staff it was like being in Groundhog Day for 23 iterations of Benning phase but with food and sleep. His most interesting assignment was as a senior advisor to an Iraqi National Police Battalion in east Baghdad for a year. After the Army, he worked as an Army civilian in Alaska, facility manager at a Pringles plant, city manager in Alaska, then retired as a Deputy State Director in Wyoming for BLM. City manager in Palmer, Alaska was the most fun by far. Nate started making beer after his first tour in Germany and has since expanded into wine and spirits. He is trying to start a tiny vineyard in the sage brush desert of northeast Nevada now. He enjoys all the activities listed by Lissa (especially the beer parts) except hiking - his knees and ankles can't handle much after 10 years of jump status late in his Army life. He can be reached at nwallace6@yahoo.com | 907-232-4380."
