    "Edited Writeup": "Tom Weiss resides in Cape Canaveral, Florida, where he recently finished a career in telecommunications focused on cellular infrastructure. Contact information includes (847) 894-8009 and tom.weiss86@gmail.com. He described his cadet experience candidly, crediting George Bond and other G1 classmates with supporting him through difficult periods. His cadet memories center less on specific events than on those peer relationships. His most significant Army assignment was with the 3rd Armored Cavalry Regiment at El Paso, where he participated in the last full maneuver REFORGER exercise in 1988 and later deployed for six months to Saudi Arabia and Iraq during Desert Shield and Desert Storm. After military service, he built a career in telecommunications, working on cellular infrastructure with companies including Motorola, Nokia, and Gogo, traveling extensively to Japan in the 1990s and contributing to industry standards development. His current interests include scuba diving, cruising in the Caribbean and Europe, and future travel plans tied to his wife’s anticipated retirement and his family includes a son and step-grandchildren."
