    "Town": "Buda",
    "State": "TX",
    "Edited Writeup": "Tom Wenneson Tom lives in Buda, Texas. He just married Holly in November 2025. He has an adopted son, Marco, who graduated from West Point in 2005 and served tours in Iraq and Afghanistan, first as Infantry then as Civil Affairs. Marco is married to Jennifer Kim, and they have two daughters and currently live in Salt Lake City where he works with Goldman Sachs. Tom was on the Sport Parachute team was everything he could hope for in terms of memories, a lifelong dream fulfilled that created great connections with teammates from all classes. One of his more vivid memories was carrying the Virginia state flag at the Army Navy game in the Rose Bowl during plebe year. He attended Fort Rucker for flight school and Apache qualification, then Fort Hood for unit formation of 5/6 Cavalry and training. He served in Germany at Wiesbaden until Desert Storm, then deployed to Saudi Arabia. Post Desert Storm, he returned to Fort Rucker and trained as an Apache instructor pilot, training pilots for two years. He completed advanced course then returned to Fort Hood (1/6 Cavalry) as Assistant S3, where he left the Army in 1995. His best assignment was Apache IP at Rucker, another dream fulfilled. In 1995, he hired into Applied Materials as a Technical Trainer teaching semiconductor manufacturing equipment operations, maintenance, and repair to major industry players, traveling much of the world in technical and supervisory roles. His most interesting role was learning to teach installation, maintenance, and operation of SEM (Scanning Electron Microscopes) which involved multiple trips to Israel. In 2009, he moved to the VOIP telecommunication industry with ShoreTel and then Mitel after acquisition, continuing in technical training and management roles. In 2019, he moved into Sales Enablement and now manages a program team building sales training and sales skills development. Tom has come to love Jesus, cooking, gardening, travel, and beer. He makes very edible BBQ smoked brisket and crazy tasty and crazy hot sauces from peppers he has grown. If you swing down south of Austin, look him up. He can be reached at tom@wenneson.com | 408-598-5634."
