    "Edited Writeup": "Eric Whipple Whips lives in Lincoln, Nebraska, about a mile from his daughter Emily, a dedicated high school math teacher who switched from elementary education to middle and high school instruction. Eric lost his wife Lori in 2022 after 29 years of marriage. His plebe company was B1. Eric's standout Army story involves executing a bold flanking maneuver during a training exercise in Germany—diverting from the expected plan and leading his platoon over a ridgeline for a surprise attack that earned praise from a visiting general. He also crawled the entire Darby Queen obstacle course at Ranger School under intense instructor pressure, which became legendary. He served as rifle platoon leader, XO, and scout platoon leader before leaving just before Desert Shield. His wildest cadet memory was being the \"victim\" on a runaway toboggan during ski patrol training that wasn't properly secured, leading to a chaotic descent down the ski slope. After the Army, he built a 35+ year pharmaceutical sales career with Sandoz (Novartis) and GlaxoSmithKline, thriving in Nebraska and underserved regions. He skis, golfs, and follows Army football closely, maintaining strong ties with company mates through reunions and shared events. Following Lori's passing, he became involved in facilitating grief share programs. He can be reached at enwhipple@gmail.com | 402-525-0464."
