    "Edited Writeup": "Randy lives in Syracuse, New York with his wife Denise. They have three children: Annemarie, 33, Christina, 30, and Rebecca, 28. Randy served in the 10th Mountain Division as the 10th Aviation Brigade S2 and 3-17 Cavalry Squadron S2, helping prepare units to deploy to the NTC. After grad school at Syracuse University, he worked in county government and served as executive director of a nonprofit soup kitchen. For the past 24 years, he has been President & CEO of MACNY, the Manufacturers Association, leading state-wide advocacy and workforce development efforts for hundreds of manufacturing companies. Syracuse will soon be home of the largest memory chipmaker in the US, Micron, which is investing $100 billion over the next 20 years. Randy attends sports events and travels. He enjoyed his time with classmates in H-1 and still enjoys getting together with them. He can be reached at rwolken@macny.org | 315-391-6674."
