    "Edited Writeup": "Scott Womack Scott lives in Union, West Virginia. His elder son Josiah graduated from VMI in 2019 and is a U.S. Army ADA Captain, married to Rachel with a daughter named Angeleena. His younger son Samuel graduated from Washington and Lee in 2021 and works as a geologist at a gold mine in Elko, Nevada. His most memorable assignment was serving as U.S. Defense Attaché to eight countries in Sub-Saharan Africa during GWOT, enjoying freedom of action with counterparts while the region remained an economy-of-force mission. During CTLT with the 2nd ACR on the Czech border, he spoke German and conducted joint patrols with the Bundesgrenzschutz and Zoll. After the Army, he bought a homestead farm in West Virginia and taught and coached at the local high school for 14 years. He recently retired from teaching and was elected to the local school board, now serving as Board President. He's also state President of the West Virginia Professional Educators, a non-union association of teachers and administrators. He serves as one of the class Volunteer Veteran Services Liaisons with WPAOG. He's interested in living history, equestrian activities, homestead life, and hunting, fishing, and foraging. He can be reached at scott_womack@hotmail.com | 304-992-4405."
