    "Edited Writeup": "Woody Woodring Woody lives in Lanham, Maryland. Woody was a plebe in A3 and graduated from G2. His favorite cadet memory was graduating. His highlight assignment was Germany in the 80s. His most interesting assignment was Afghanistan in 2006, his most taxing was the Pentagon, his assignment with the most work was Fort Bragg, and his best location was Hawaii. His career path was not a straight line to retirement—he was RIFed in the 90s, then came back in after 9-11, followed by Afghanistan and the DC area where he had the interesting fortune to work for the executive branch, the legislative branch, and the Pentagon.  He had a heart attack in 2014 and open heart surgery at age 50 and is still recovering. He retired after 30 years and went into commercial real estate, working on low income housing for seven years. He sold everything and now focuses on his health and traveling. He has been to 50 countries and would like to see a few more. Woody likes to travel. He can be reached at walter.woodring@gmail.com."
