    "Edited Writeup": "Paul lives in Valrico, Florida. His plebe company was D4, graduating from D1. He has three children and five granddaughters. He is married to Christina, whom he met at a Mount St. Mary's party during Firstie year where he volunteered as the keg attendant. He remembers the advantage of living along Cullum Road, allowing him to see Christina and talk to her from the windows.  He served armor and stayed at Fort Knox for five years, with frequent travel to training events such as NTC, Fort Bliss, and REFORGER. His major highlight was being assigned to a DARPA effort involving SIMNET and large-scale combat simulation used to run repeated scenarios based on Middle East terrain and logistics assumptions—he asserted the work informed senior decision-making during Desert Storm planning. He left active duty as Desert Storm unfolded and transitioned via Cameron-Brooks-era recruiting into pharmaceutical sales at Pfizer, initially working the Duke area. He stayed about 19 years at Pfizer, moving through sales and management, then moved across several firms (including BMS, UCB, Diplomat/Optum, and Heritage) in progressively more specialized federal and VA-facing roles, building a niche as a national account leader for federal accounts, VA systems, and military bases. His current company provides emergency medicines to the VA. He emphasizes strong ongoing contact with his company classmates through a standing text thread and enjoyed a Scotland trip involving several of them. He is building a family retreat on property called Hidden Creek Ranch that is themed like an old west town, designed to host around 40 people as a potential mini-reunion destination for D1. The property features walking trails, river time, and sharks teeth hunting. He can be reached at pworsfold@tampabay.rr.com | 813-352-0482."
