    "Edited Writeup": "Lissa lives in Highland Falls, New York. She jokes \"I am not a breeder!\" when it comes to children. Her plebe company was A2, graduating from I1. Her most memorable cadet experience was flying the entire Corps of Cadets to California and marching in the Rose Bowl parade—or if not the Rose Bowl parade, some kind of parade. That joy stopped after the first 38 seconds when Navy began stomping the hell out of them. She was an aviator and did not love being on Jump Status at Bragg, but did enjoy her command there. She also loved commanding the Army's High Altitude Rescue Team (HART) in Fairbanks, Alaska. After the Army, she devoted herself to becoming a scholar, went to graduate school, earned her PhD, and then returned to West Point to teach. She's been there ever since and it has been a joy. She has dreams of being a motorcycle mechanic and riding across the world on a motorcycle. Her ideal classmate activities include: 1) Supe's Boat tour on the Hudson with beer, 2) An afternoon at the Tin Barn Brewing Company in Chester, 3) A hike in the Black Rock Forest, and 4) An afternoon at Westy's in Highland Falls drinking beer together. She can be reached at lissa.young@westpoint.edu | 617-947-5021."
